Then the screen popped up with the option "I'm already here".  I pre-ordered from my office so I was NOT there yet, and didn't do anything with it.  Got to Mac, to the pick up counter, and they didn't have my order?!?!  I looked at the app again.  Now, I'm there, so I clicked the "I'm already here".  Well, then it asked me if I wanted curb-side pick up or in-store; then if I wanted eat-in or take out.  Clicked on the take-out, and then voila, my order was showing on the display monitor (on the bottom of the queue)!!  So, my order was never sent beforehand!  Genius...

content: This app is complete trash. I cannot log in to view offers, there are never mailer coupons anymore, and it will never load in a restaurant on the rare time it does log in. Complete waste of time downloading. Love McDonalds, but if I can get cheaper food elsewhere on the run, I am going to go there instead. This app must have been designed to not work, it's the only way it could be this bad.
It's completely broken. I cannot select a location. It keeps bringing up the location picking menu after I pick one.

Here are the problems I encountered in my order today: 1. At the moment of checking it, the price increased by 0.40$. Not much, but no reason given. 2. The order was submitted to another restaurant than the one I chose. 3. I get to the other restaurant, they tell me they can't process mobile orders.  The app is also very slow and unintuitive.  1/5; won't use again.

Do not bother with this app. The app appears fine but has several issues. Quite often the app crashes, shows errors when looking at promotions, and will sometimes not even fulfull an order. The biggest issue is the serious lack of security when it comes to your financial information. Personally, my account was breached and $150 spent without my permission. When the issue was brought to McDonald's attention, I was told that it was my problem and wouldn't apologize or admit a security problem.

Needing to sign in each time is not very convenient. Is it due to security issues? Also, the app deals have become noticeably less frequent and not that great compared to when I first started using it. I haven't received any app deals in the past 3 weeks. I suppose they have enough people using it now, but if the only benefit is that I can order ahead, then it's not really worth the space on my phone. The Burger King app has better deals; better app rating, too.

The UI is okay but it has a $40 limit (not even enough for lunch of one adult and two teens) and has no idea of items that aren't available at the location chosen... at least not until I pulled into that curbside pickup at which point it immediately told me that two of my three meals weren't available and the only option being to continue with the single remaining one. Horrible.

After logging in, I can't tap on anything. I'm on the main menu screen (where it says "view offers" and "start your order") but none of the buttons work. Not even the ones at the bottom of the screen. It's like I'm trying to interact with a still image. I have tried relogging and reinstalling. Edit: Tried reinstalling once more. Now I can't even log in. I can't tap anything. You would think a corporation as big as McDonald's would be able to spend a few dollars on pushing a fix for these things

replyContent: Hi Beverly, we're sorry to hear your mobile order did not work. In order to remove your credit card information please follow these steps: Open the 'More' menu, then select 'Profile'; 'Payment Methods' and long-press/swipe-left on the section where your name and 4-digits of the CC are shown, when prompted, click on 'Remove' and confirm.

replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. This is a known issue that we are currently working on to resolve. Stay tuned for an update with a permanent fix.

content: Used to work fine up until last update now when you open it it's completely Frozen and locked up and can't do anything I get notification saying I have new deals but I can't use them

App does not work well It currently doesn't let me log in or even reset my password even though I know I entered it correctly. It doesn't refresh itself either, so even when you complete an order it still leaves it in the system. So say if you go back later it tells you that you can't use the same offer twice, but I ordered that like 3 hours before! App needs a lot of development. Very poor for such a big company.

App constantly crashes. Wont let you pre order until your actually in the parking lot so it doesnt really get you ahead of anyone in line anyways. App doesnt even know the menu and wont let you order breakfast sandwiches during lunch even though they are available. I don't understand how a company can update an app that runs like garbage and screw it up even worse. Thanks for the response, as noted in my comment already the "I'm already here" button doesn't work until I'm sitting in the lot.
replyContent: Hi Trevor, thanks for the comment! Please make sure you've updated to the latest version of the app. We've now added a new 'I'm Already Here' button so you can choose your pick-up method and we'll start preparing your order earlier.

content: The app worked in 2019. But in Aug 2020, I can't get past the initial screen. One time after a min, it said I was offline (I wasn't). ------- The review below was written 2018--11-24: The app is very unreliable. I've had problems ordering. For the past week, I could never login, even after resetting my password. I had to uninstall and reinstall the app to be able to login.

The McDonald's in The Pas Manitoba, worst run McDonald's as far as I have noted in my travels. My friends and I are use to the following one of two orders not right when we order and when complain we get U do not care attitude. Small town no other option. That is why I will only rate your organization as a 2 or 3.

Raised my review from 1* to 3*, as the app is much more stable now. Unfortunately, the quality of the coupons offered plummeted. Previously, the deals meant I picked McDonald's over all other fast food chains. Now that the deals have become so poor, I have no additional motivation for going there, and find myself going to Burger King and Wendy's more.
replyContent: Hi there. We're sorry for the inconvenience and currently working on this issue. Please stay tuned for an update!

content: App is broken, saying email doesn't exist even though I get sent emails all the time. Tried to set up new account, claims no internet connection.

When I first started to use the app everything was fine and then it started to not give me details telling me that its unavailable and saying that is temporarily having difficulties . It always had me logged in and it was convenient but now I go through the drive thru and I have to stop what I'm doing just to log in because for some reason it doesn't keep my login information anymore . so I'm never sure if I have a dealer not because of all the errors that that it gives me .
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email address, wifi or cellular connection, steps you took to get any errors, screenshots/error codes at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: Terrible UX. You're never sure of which restaurant you're actually ordering from until it's too late, and you're never sure of where you are in the ordering process. Sent in orders to the wrong location twice already despite selecting a different location (or at least that's what I thought). The app is also really buggy in that offers don't always load properly, and will sporadically log you out. Also doesn't contain mailer coupons. Overall, I expected more from McDs.

Issues with app Mostly I have no problems with the app and find it useful when needed, however this morning I was trying to order three different items for me my partner and my kid and try as I might, it would not allow one breakfast with apple juice and one with orange juice. I tried as many different ways as I could think of but it would still just duplicate one or the other instead. This needs to be corrected as if I hadn't noticed, it would be very annoying.

My first time using the app and I hated it. My biggest problem was making the transaction, to pay for my meal. I never got it of course. When it shows you your options for paying the meal, there is no option for paying debit. Since I'm new to the online delivery process I tried researching if my card had a ccv or a expirey date since those were the qualifications of paying. since its a debit card there was no expirey date, and the app had no other options beyond credit, visa, or any other payment method, nor did it show an option for cash. I'm extremely disappointed, and wish I hadn't spent over a half an hour looking for what the app asked for. For people who use debit or cash, don't use this app, your better off walking over and getting it yourself.

What a stupid app it is. It's now Covid-19 and I walked down to the nearest McDonald for 10 min. tried to make a curbside order and it failed. It doesn't accept orders exceeding 25 dollars. Literally played around the app and finally it passed curbside hours and I walked back with my empty hands. No way to contact that location's customer service. I had my vehicle and I just don't want to bother driving because it's too close; but what if a person doesn't have a car and want to order something?

Entering the order works fine but the last step this past few weeks had been annoying. The system tells me I am not connected to the internet or I have to restart; I try with my data or the WiFi at McDonald's and both do not work. Other times, it connects you to a different restaurant, even after you explicitly select the restaurant you are at. Overall, annoying.

as much as I enjoy using this app, it has its pros and cons. pro, the ordering and the reorder features are easy and quick to use. it also got nice offers to kick start new users too! cons, I truly wish this app would let me pay for the office lunch and have someone else go pickup the order without having to give them my phone. also, on many occasions they give me the wrong orders. when I'm parked at #3, don't give me #2's order... not convenient at all for this.
replyContent: Hi Goryee, thanks for the feedback. We can use this information as we continue to evolve and improve the app. Stay tuned for updates!

content: Freezes for Offers. So you want to add an offer to your order? The app makes it sooo difficult and it freezes for 4 or 5 minutes. It's like it doesn't want to give you a deal. Also I order from the same McDonald's every time but this app can't remember that. Twice it changed the location on me after I picked my usual location and switched me to one that I was passing by on my way to work. Didn't notice until after I paid, waste of food and money. Good app for simple stuff but full of bugs.

This is such a frustrating app. In the past 3 mornings I have bought 4 coffees. When the coffees are scanned in via scanner, the app does not update. The only way I get credit for purchases is when the QR code is manually entered. It also seems that no one at store level has any knowledge of the app, which makes it equally frustrating.

I am hooked. Both on the easy-to-use ordering and the McDonald's food. I have used it a few times where I go in to pick up a carry out order. So much faster then drive thru at rush times. The staff are not use to that as I catch them running out the door to the mobile order parking spots with my order. May try the waiting outside option.
replyContent: Hi Trevor, thank you for your review! Weâ€™re glad to hear you had a great experience with our app and with mobile ordering.

content: App was okay but for whatever reason became unresponsive to any interaction whatsoever. I attempted restarting the application but it didn't solve the issue.

Besides the known issue of how the app behaves on some Android devices, I am now being charged for orders that are not completed on the app. When I select "take out" the app says there's a problem but the charge still shows on my bank card and the order does not go through to the kitchen. I use the app for its convenience every day but will not be going forward until this issue is resolved. Clearing the app's cache and/or reinstall does not resolve this new problem.
replyContent: Hi Jeff, we are sorry to hear this. We'd like to discuss this further, please give us a call at 1-888-424-4622 (Monday to Friday 9:00am-7:00pm EST, Saturday 10:00am-6:00pm EST) so we can further investigate.ï»¿

content: Have tried this app 4 times on my old phone and now this is my second time with my new phone. So far it's 0/6 on two different devices. Every time the folks working don't have the order in the system and have to order and wait. Which is fine, but thought this app was made to reduce wait and order times. App looks good but that's it, it doesn't do what it's meant to do. Hope it's fixed.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for sharing this issue with us. Please email us with more details at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: I've been logged out of the app randomly and it keeps on jumping back to the closest McDonald's as I put together my order even though that's not I want. Last time I used it, I set my location and when I ordered it jumped back to the closest McDonald's forcing me to take another 15 minute detour. On top of that, the location wasn't even accurate as the McDonald's it sent me to moved another block west.

This app is the worst online order app. You cannot complete the order unless your phone is physically on the premises. Makes it's very difficult to order unless you are the one picking up the order. My husband then downloaded the app and logged in on his phone so he could pick it up. This then locked our account and we still could not complete the order. 30 minutes later and we've given up.

It has been complete garbage over the last month. Error after error message. Can't even login in anymore. Did a reinstall and tried to reset password and all I get is "this is not the correct verification code" when it absolutely is. Worked great at one time. Sucks now. (edit) Improved rating from 1 star to 3 because your customer service is solid. Someone contacted me & App is finally working again. Need to fix the Android issues though. 2018 was great. Poor start to 2019.
replyContent: Hi Cheryl, thank you for your continued feedback. As we work to resolve ongoing issues we can use your feedback to improve. Stay tuned for updates!

content: When it works, it's ok. A little tedious with lots of back and forth to make decisions about your order and using coupons and customizing. But the biggest problem is that more often then not, when I open the app it is simply hung/frozen on the main screen and I can't scroll and no options function to see offers, or move to my account or anything. Trend seems 100% of the time when I am at home, regardless of on wifi or cell network only. Some improvement when I'm elsewhere but still not reliable. Furthermore, when I arrive at a McDs for pick up, it's very slow to figure out my location. Same with when I want to make an order at a different location- app seems very reluctant to let me plan an order for somewhere that is not my closest option.

They have used to work well. But I went up to the window after making an order. I didn't use the app to make my order though. I tried to select my payment and it would not give me the option to pay unless I use the app to order. Pretty inconvenient. Tim Hortons you can click on the pay now and you don't even need your card. Now that is convenience. I should not have to make an order to be able to pay on the app

Generally good but specific problem with mobile order and WiFi connection. I do a mobile order and drive to the store. My phone is connected to McDonald's WiFi but not logged in as it needs manual acceptance. I don't want to do that as I am just driving through. But my order doesn't show up in your system as the order is waiting for wifi connection to go through. Have wasted a lot of time at the window many times resolving this issue.

This is the worst app ever! You have to open/close and open a 2nd time for it to work and that does not always work. I've had to pay full price multiple times because the app won't show any current offers when I know for a fact there are offers available. McD's come on and hire a app developer that can actually do the job right! This app is just frustrating and terrible.

So it was good at first. The app bugs if you add a coupon to your cart and it expires. There is no way to remove it and you can not add a new coupon or delete the expired one. It simply errors with no way to fix it. Plus I'm not getting any offers that match my tastes like I used to. The app used to constantly send me offers for things I ate often but now I barely get anything. I've found myself using this app less and less. I've just Uninstalled to try and get rid of this glitch.
replyContent: Hi Saphire, thanks for your feedback. Please try following these steps: log out of your My McD's account, clear app cache, uninstall and reinstall the app, restart your device and log in back again. If you're still experiencing issues please send an email to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: I, too, keep getting the error message everyone's talking about. Now that I'm home, I can see all of the offers I missed out on when I was at the restaurant. Very frustrating. :'( P.S. I'd love if there could be a button where the restaurant would start preparing my food before I got there, so that I don't have to wait so long, like they do with the Starbucks app. That would really make this one better! (Once the issue with the error code is corrected, of course!)

Horrible. Rewards are horrible, app never opens the first time, you can choose which location you want to order from until your close to it and the food doesn't even start being prepared until your there. I don't see the benefit of this. More often than not my order didn't go through and I end up ordering again and paying twice. It's extremely slow and jus tsp poorly made for such a large company.

The screen stayed frozen most of the time, not allowing me to do anything with it. Furthermore, when it does work, it places an order, but claims I'm not at the restaurant. And so I have to show the purchase order code to the cashier. But the cashier says the order # is not in their system and so cannot process it. Honestly .... this app is frustrating.  If not for the occasional free offers, I'd give up on this altogether.
Ultra easy to use and very fair rewards. It's not 100% perfect but not having to pull out my card and tap it all the time is more than worth it!

This app is very frustrating in its current state, every time the app closes your logged out and apparently on my phone (huawei p20 pro) there is a bug where you need to uninstall then reinstall the app in order to log in again. It's a complete waist of time. Also on a side note your account password can only be 8-12 characters long so I had to come up with a new short password for my account, what kind of password can only be a maximum of 12 characters... It's ridiculous...

Useless app. I have to go through the whole picking process for each item I add, and then, I'm told my order won't be prepared until I show up. What's the point? I can just show up and verbally, simply tell them what I want, and they'll get it ready,... because I'm there. Oddly, a time saver. I live 3 minutes walk, maybe four if I drag my feet, away from the mc Donald (gas station drive through), at the other corner of my street. BRA-VO

I loved the app! It offered so many McDonalds bargains, and on a daily basis. There were extra BOGO's, discounts and combos.    Unfortunately when my 7 inch tablet broke (slid off a chair onto floor at McDonalds)  I replaced it with a 10 inch RCA WINDOWS tablet. It never occurred to me that this would be the end of my MyMcD bargains. Apparently the MyMcD app only works with Android devices and there no plans to create a Microsoft compatible one.  I find it very aggravating....I'm missing out on so many McD deals..and who likes paying full price when they don't have to. The App deals are not available anywhere else.

Have used this app for months. After last update I could no longer pay through the app. It gave no alert and then I was told at the drivethrough window that my card was declined. Now App freezes before I can place an order. Poorly designed, non functional app. To bad because I used to use it all the time, and if the contact free payment option doesn't work any more, I'll be going to Wendy's instead from now on. Somebody should get fired over this nonsense. If I could give zero stars I would.
Can't open, it just force closes constantly

I like the offers in this app BUT I have had to re-install 3 times. It is simply the worst written app in the play store and should be removed. Works a couple times and then stops...you can make an order but on the final step when you arrive, an error occurs. McDonalds employees tell me lots if people are having the same issue. PLEASE MAKE THE OFFERS AVAILABLE VIA E-MAIL!

The latest build is garbage. You have to re-login everytime you open the app to view the available offers. The GPS is wonky and takes ages to connect. The Starbucks app locates you within seconds. And lastly, the offers themselves are so meh now. They used to be more enticing to use b/c of the savings ($1 Big Macs). Now it's best to wait for the BOGO coupons to be released online in your province.

Just went to open the app and it says it's no longer supported, please upgrade to the latest version in your app store. But it keeps bringing me back to the app store to the app that is no longer supported, with no new download /updates. For a response back super quickly that the issue has been resolved. Thank for the speedy response!
replyContent: Hi there, we're so sorry for any inconvenience this has caused. We're happy to inform you that the issue on the app has now been resolved. Thanks for your patience.

content: Your app is horrible.  I am constantly getting the message that you are having issues on your end, please close the app and try again.  I have a brand new S9 and there is no way it is my phone.  I cant tell you how many times I have opened the app while in line and have not had it work properly.  If you are going to offer discounts and freebies to your customers only through the app then you need to make sure it is bulletproof.  I hope you do an upgrade soon.

Well things just keep getting worse. Now I have to login every time and once logged in I get an error 28300 message. can't scan my coffees. extremely frustrating! Since the last update it keeps crashing and when I try to get my coffee stamp scan it won't show up. I have to go through multiple pages before my scan coffee shows up. replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email address, wifi or cellular connection, steps you took to get any errors, screenshots/error codes at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: this app works 20% of the time, the other 80% it freezes on the login screen no matter how many times you uninstall, clear cache, etc. I cant believe this isnt fixed yet, this has been happening since February. My friends experience this issue also. This has got to be one of the worst apps ever, it feels like there is no one even remotely attempting to work on this issue as their has never been an update although it is usually stated. Please fix this.

Trash app. This morning I placed an order at the location I always go to in the same mall I work at but the app ordered it at another close by location which I have never visited. And I could not go pick it up.

Frustrating app. Food isn't made until you arrive at store, defeating the purpose of ordering ahead. You still have to wait in line for them to make it. App doesn't close my order after completion. I've had multiple 'ghost' orders because I drive by the McDonald's and it 'completes' my order again from 6 days ago. If I ordered breakfast items yesterday, it won't let me order lunch items. App itself is slow and laggy on every device I've tried. Offers are lacklustre, the old coupons were better.
Cannot add payment option. Cannot make purchases until they fix this.

The worst app I've ever used, constantly breaks and asks for restarts, but the restarts don't do anything. To make things worse, now McDonald's is forcing you to register to get deals. I can't even register because the activate button in the email they send you doesn't activate anything! I guess I'm going to A&W for supper tonight. I wish I could rate this app negative stars, I've dealt with its glitches for a year now, and now I can't even use it at all.

No more issues with the app saying i'm not using the latest version. When it works it's great, biggest problem now is after I pick up my order from the store it doesn't clear out of the phone. Even the next day it's still in there and causes messages about modifying an existing order in progress. No, that order ended over 18 hours ago.
replyContent: Sorry for the inconvenience but this has been solved. Please try updating the app just in time to earn McCafe Mobile Rewards!

content: Every single time, without fail, the app has a problem and I have to log out and log back in to fix the issue. EVERY SINGLE TIME. Also, when I place an order for take out at the drive thru, it happens often that the worker doesn't have my order on their screens, and this after I've selected the right restaurant, food, offers, and checked out properly... This is a big hassle....

DO NOT DOWNLOAD! The app is only good for coupons. The mobile ordering is terrible. My order was not going through so I had to order multiple times. Eventually I had to speak to the cashier. When I went to check my credit card statement, I was charged for all the orders that supposedly did not go through. Now I have to deal with going through my bank to be refunded. You would think a large franchise like McDonald's would be able to pay someone to make a working app.

Have to log in every single time I open the app?! No setting to remember my email? In the drive thru lane typing out my email and trying to remember my password every time, only to see "no offers available at this time". Online ordering? "Sorry, we're experiencing technical difficulties". So glad I spent 5 minutes trying to log in :/ What a useless app. I'll go to Timmies instead next time.
Works every time

Frustrating. Keeps picking a farther location, and tells me that I'm "not there yet", even when I'm in the restaraunt. Who would know better than me? So what's the point in ordering ahead, when you can't place your order? That needs to be fixed. If I say "I'm here", then I'm there! So place my order already. Would be cool if it was smarter
Functional- sometimes store locator freezes. Have to go back a page or two to get it to recognize your location.
My email is correct. Even checked spam folder. Resent confirmation many times and has not been sent to my email. Waited over half hour.

This app barely works. And by barely, i mean less than 5% of the time. If i could leave zero stars, i would. Nothing but "there was an error on our end, restart the app" or "something went wrong try again later". Left email feedback, website feedback and Facebook message. Nothing but crickets. Hire some people that know what what they're doing!
replyContent: Hi Will,  thanks for sharing this issue with us. Please email us with more details at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: The app is done very well. Offers and Orders work well. It is missing the option to apply paper-based mail/print discounts. That's a big one, that must be enabled asap since I can use them at the kiosks! Also, the App Update process has bugs sometimes. Often, I am logged-out and need to login again after an App Update, and sometimes the Offers and Orders don't work and I have to uninstall and reinstall the app. Not good.

content: This app is always 'experiencing technical difficulties' when ordering, app then refuses to do anything and you are forced to restart. Restarting the app never fixes the issue, it will just run you in a loop. I have only successfully placed an order through the app once. Handy to have coupons when there are none mailed out, but they're not as good.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email, type of phone, OS, app version, wifi or cell connection, and screenshots/error codes to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: Ok, when it works. It only works half the time. It is very frustrating to slowly enter an order only to be told your mcdonalds doesnt serve big macs anymore and have to cancel it. This is after me spends weeks trying to get it to accept my billing info. And waiting 2-5 seconds every time you click an option while it retrieves the menu(which hasnt changed all year), just in case it changedin the last two seconds.

DO NOT USE THIS APP!!! My order was sent to another restaurant over 20 minutes away from the one I picked to order from. Since I was working as a bus driver, I could not pick up my order at the new location. Was assured the order would be refunded within 5 business days. Calling back 2 weeks later, I was told they could not refund my fee, was offered coupons by snail mail instead, which never arrived. It's been over a month since I called.

Security is key. Honestly it doesn't matter how good the features of an app are. If the only option for payment is through credit card stored within the app then there should be better security. Passwords are limited to 8 - 12! And there's been news recently that if someone breaches your account then you have to sort it out with your credit card provider. I think the convenience doesn't outweigh the risk.
Credit card does not add to the app. It worked at first, but then the app shows an error every time I try to save the card number in the app

Easily one of the most frustrating apps I have ever used. The interaction and design is clunky and unintuitive. several occasions we try to order on the drive hoping to order before arrival, but end up quitting several minutes after arriving simply join the line up. Out of 6 attempts to use, I have managed to order twice after several minutes of struggling. Consistently receive a pop up dialog with "We are experiencing a problem on our side".

content: I ended up going to Wendy's.   Why?  The app stopped responding to touch.   Everything else worked.  Just not the app.  I figured it was old or something so I restarted and reinstalled.   It worked! Until I actually pulled into the pick up spot.  Then it froze again.  Tried reinstalling. Still didn't work.   I have an open order right now so I'm hoping it'll just timeout and drop off so I don't get charged because there also doesn't seem to be a way to modify or cancel things once an order is placed.   Not that I could anyway since the app is still frozen.    Plus the random changes to the options available for everything severely limits what I can do to a sandwich now.   I can't even add mayo to a lot of sandwiches.   I'm sad because when the app first launched it was great.  But it slowly turned to junk.

 ï»¿

content: This works so infrequently that I've stopped using it and will be uninstalling it. The UX is just awful. I've never seen another app that doesn't save any log in information whatsoever. Not only that but I usually have trouble getting table service to work. It's more trouble than the discounts are worth, and since I've become vegetarian, there's virtually nothing there for me. They even got rid of their grilled cheese sandwiches. Seriously, don't waste your time with this app.

Pleasant app when it works, but there are some issues. For one, when my order is complete, why do I need to manually delete it afterwards? Sometimes, it takes minutes to 'refresh' before you can use it. The one thing that bugs me the most though is that you pay through the app, it gives you a virtual receipt and when you go to pick up, they tell you the card was declined (so you manually pay with the one the app has declined). Why doesn't the app tell you its declined?

Garbage. App doesn't work. The app made me sign up to view the offers in my area (address or postal code would have worked) then after signing up I had to verify my email for some reason before I could look at anything on the app, because there is apparently a lot of McFraud going on?? Clicked on the link to activate my account and was redirected to a url with a page tell me my account isn't active and I need to click the link in my email?? I literally had just clicked on said link. Do not use...
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for bringing this to our attention. Please send us an email to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: It use to work great when no one had it...the past month or two I've noticed a lot more promos and ads mentioning the app and all of a sudden it crashes every time I try to use it now...It logs off like it's a banking app or something and makes you log back in...okay fine. The issue is when you put in yhe right password it says it's wrong and you reset, drove me crazy but I did it...finally tried using that pass on a diff device and it worked. Next time it didnt work on the other device either... Ended up realizing I need to uninstall and reinstall every time i want to use it...waste of time...best part was coming here and realizing its an issue a lot of people have been having for months now but Mcd doesn't care. Thought you were trying to get digital and stay strong...wouldnt want that share price to drop because people are looking at other options while you guys are pushing a platform that won't work consistently.

Today the app tells me to upgrade? Sorry this APP version is no longer compatible. Please upgrade to the latest version. There is no newer version! I uninstalled, then reinstalled with no joy. content: This app is horrible . It used too work fine up until a mounth ago . At first it kept loggimg me out while I was using it and now I can't even get past the home screen . Nothing budges . I try too click on "view offers" or the menu bar and nothing happens . At all . I can't scroll down , I can't do anything and it pisses me off because when I want too get an item or order at a certain location it just does not work . content: The app is a bit buggy. It showed some of the things in my shopping cart as $0, which they weren't, and when I went to pickup my order it told me to pay extra. But I was able to edit my order there and then in 30 seconds and they finally ended up charging me only for the final order that I picked up. So I'm satisfied. I get that you're aware of the crashing issue on Android, but this is ridiculous. Doesn't make sense to me that a fix hasn't been found yet. When it doesn't work, it is a frustrating experience. eg selecting a location that isn't the closest to you is an exercise is patience. very frustrating app. i got a push notification regarding free fries that i click when i go to the store. it opens the app and the promotion is gone. as well another time i tried to use the app at the pay kiosks and it doesn't work and there is no way to tell until you make it to the payment screen. other times it crashes. very disappointed in this app.

Recently can't add any of my cards. Says error please add card later. None of my parents accounts work either, so that's 0-3. App is useless now. Written my postal code multiple ways, deleted the app, nothing.

Is there 0 stars? App stopped working, uninstalled and reinstalled. Order being fulfilled at wrong restaurant. I have always been ordering from the same place near my work, so I can pick it up and go straight to the office.

absolutely horrible app. does not function. I cannot use coupons that are mobile order only because it keeps giving me an error message when I try to save my card details. it is telling me that "Ontario" is not a province when I try to file a complaint. it is telling me that the 24hr McDonald's location nearest to me is closed at high noon. it barely works at all if you don't want to turn on your location settings. abysmal app, I don't know why it is on the app store when it doesn't function.

Absolutely awful. It bugged out when I denied location services and told it to stop asking. Then when I enabled location, the app goes into my phone's settings page and doesn't do anything. I have to exit the app to back out. Honestly the worst app I've downloaded in the 8 years of having a phone.

As it is, it's pointless to order ahead if the order will not be processed until you're within a few hundred feet proximity, and even then won't be submitted until you confirm in the app what pickup location you prefer. content: The original app was much better, I was paying in app, deal done, then I go to store and pick up my food! Now it is too confusing, last night I ordered few thing, gone there, they don't know what I am talking about, had to order again in store, now I have 3 pending charges on my card, one for $48.27 and 2 for $44.44, stupid and ridiculous! All that hassle, stress, and headache for such simple task of ordering from a fast-food restaurant, never again!

When the app works, it's great. Sad to say that I've put in hours with McDonald's technical support, trying make this app function, but I keep hitting one bug after another. My current ticket about a failure at checkout has gone unanswered for 9 days since I gave them all the technical details they had requested. Sorry McDonald's. I'm trying help you, but you're not helping me. Wish I could be more positive. If you fix the app, I'll revise my review.

App crashes about 50% of the time upon opening. If you use a coupon from the app at the kiosk and the app crashes you lose the coupon. In store has no capability to correct the problem. After 3 months now the app randomly tells me the store I am standing in is currently closed. And it won't let me order breakfast items at 8am as this item is not available at this time of day. Bacon and egg mcmuffin, really??!!! Thought this would get better, not worse.
replyContent: Hi there. We're sorry for the inconvenience and currently working on this issue. Please stay tuned for an update!

content: Love the offers you get through the app.... When the app ACTUALLY WORKS! About 80% of the time this app just constantly fails and says its on their end... SO FIX IT!! I've had a number of time when I want to use a coupon, but "oops. the app is down". Crappy app, but good offers EDIT: NOW Mcdonalds seems to want to entice people to get their credit card info stolen by making certain offers that were once usable in store, mobile order offers only. So save $2 on $10 then have your info stolen!

The curbside pickup feature is completely useless. The restaurants ignore the orders when they come in and only serve the drive-through. Averaged over 30 minutes wait times, and counted 27 and 33 cars served at the drive through, respectively, while I waited. In the end I still had to go to the drive through to get my order. Get your act together!!!

WARNING. THIS APP MAY CHARGE YOU TWICE AND WILL NOT REFUND YOU. YOU WILL HAVE TO TALK TO YOUR BANK THUS MAKING THIS APP 100% NOT WORTH IT. Every single penny you save isnt worth getting double charged even once and having to fight it.

You really need to improve the favorites and allow us to NAME locations. Addresses are poor - especially when there are a few in the area (e.g. near me there are two within walking distance - one separate and one within Wallymart). My ideal is to 'order something' at a specific location quickly. It is just a pain sometimes - it always points you to the nearest and going to favorites - you have to remember the address. What if there are 3 on Sheppard and you cannot remember which is which? Such a small improvement would go far.

Worst food app ever. Cannot accomplish anything you can't do by going inside or to the drive through. Have been getting error problems on their side when arriving to the restaurant without my wallet so i had to go back home hungry and they still charged me the order so i had to wait 3 days to be refunded for something i didn't even eat. Sometimes the app simply freezes so you just can't use it. Very poorly made app. I do not recommend using this.

This app is unreliable! For most of the day, I can't access my offers then, when I'm finally able to make an order on the app, I get to McDonald's and the app won't give me my order number . It tells me, if I'm having difficulty, take this reference number to the counter, when I do that, the employees tell me they cannot help me without their order number! I go back and forth for over 20 minutes and in the end I can't use the offer for my purchase! The app and the customer service are awful!

app is very glitchy, every time I try to view my offers it gives me the error message "sorry, we're having some issues on our end. please restart the app and try again" but restarting app doesn't work. I have to uninstall and reinstall the app any time I want to actually use it. poor user experience but at least I'm eating mcdonalds less because of it!

content: For the second time, I was able to order but when I get to the window I am told that my payment was declined. There are no issues with my card. The only solution they give is to delete and re-install the app but that does not fix the credit card issue. I looks like the credit card fraud checks are declining cards due to fraud.

*update. Ok now it doesn't work at all. So I'm reinstalling again. And it won't accept my previous credentials, so I'm resetting my password (again). Very glitchy app. Does not seem to synch well with the reality of what's going on, meaning it thinks places are closed when they are open or the menu is breakfast when it is dinner. absolutely broken lately. offers aren't great to begin with, but now they never load. i have it on 2 phones, same situation. days there's about app issue, and to restart. does nothing. sometimes it'll will come back with offers, only to lose them moments later. it's especially annoying when the app is pushing notifications for offers that it won't display

content: I'm trying to log in for the deal of the day. It tells me I need to upgrade the app and to go to the play store. I do that and there is no update available. content: When I first installed this app I thought it was fantastic! Then you changed it and it hasn't worked right since! I am NOT impressed. Don't recommend it anymore.

I've had to complain 3 times in the last 3 months after waiting 20 minutes for my order, seeing people who ordered after me get their order before me. Plus when you order with the app you don't get a receipt number so you can't even formaly complain to McDonald's. Bottom line, waste of time.

The Mc Donald's restaurant didn't have the Filet-o-Fish and the sides couldn't be matched to the menu. My wife is pesceterian, so there was no real alternative offer. The staff was friendly and offered kind of a solution after I had to complain. In the end we ate cold food though.

content: Horrible user experience. Sends orders to wrong location for pickup, even though you specifically select a location before ordering. Uninstalling & reinstalling worked. Working great now! Great cust service

content: Complete garbage. Wouldn't let me use coupon codes. Wouldn't let me remove my credit card. Upon opening the app a second time, it froze until I closed it. But, to be fair, every now and again you get a goodie like a free coffee or burger.

This initial process takes upwards to 60-90 secs and repeated refreshes or shutdowns and restarts of the app. Once connected, the app works well and allows for order entry and payment with choice of pickup options. Overall the app is decent and I find ordering to be pretty easy. Adding common items as favorites makes ordering my morning coffee quick and painless. What I don't like is when i arrive and indicate I'm at the store I'll get a notice that it "doesn't appear I've arrived yet". This is a major annoyance with this app. If I'm sitting in the parking lot I know I'm there and don't need an app to tell me I'm not. Sometimes it takes 3-4 tries for this to clear. No other complaints really.

Map location does not work, always pick other locations, and can't change it

Not worth the download!! Fustating and time lost!! Tried to install my payment option only to come back as error. Called their support line. After 20 minutes , the support was useless!! content: It's long time that I couldn't sign in with the app to use it. every single time it freeze. it's always loading my account with jumping fries symbol, but nothing happen. content: While I appreciate savings, the issue lies within the app's internal communication. Periodically unable to view offers, requiring to reauthenticate and failing to do so. This is far from the only low review for this app; issues are known for months with no implemented update to address them.

Used to be good. Coupons have gone down hill fast. Many have specific requirements now (must be used in Walmart location or in-reataraunt only) and less quality coupons overall. Mobile ordering was a disaster. Restaraunts never got it right. Always ended in confusion and longer waits. I'll wait a few weeks to see if its just a phase they roll through on deals, but otherwise will delete app.

Lots of little annoying bugs that could easily be resolved by a patch and auto update. Please.

content: Useless. They don't make your order until you are physically parked or in the line at the drive through. content: Wow, is this a bad app. Ordered a meal for my mom to pickup for lunch as she forgot her lunch at home. Added payment details, made order, everything was going good. I tried ordering meals for my family and I at 4am (jetlag) , on the app it said it was open for breakfast, so as we sent our order it said it was ready for us and even had our order number ready. We went to pick it up and they told us there is no breakfast right now! That they only have muffins and coffee! If there is no breakfast at a certain time period maybe don't put the options open online and write online when things are available so people don't go all the way out for nothing!

Been using the app for years no issues. Suddenly 2 months ago ..my payments were not acceptes due to "fraud" . So i went to the drive thru and used the exact same card as what I have registered in the app...it was accepted! Today I tried again and got the same message. I use that credit card for all of my purchases. Your app is broken. My business goes elsewhere now...like Wendy's.

Clever app. I was trying to order something ahead on my way to queens station, but I realized the order was assigned to union station without even asking me for confirmation. Yes thats where I took the subway and that is why the app is so clever. I had to make another order then my last order had been labelled as "complete" and I could not use the offer again.

As convenient as it can be, this app can also be quite laggy and slow when ordering. I don't like how items left in the cart from a previous order is not automatically removed. This means you have to remove the items manually before you can make an actual order. Finally, this app should have 2-step verification. It's absolutely ridiculous how shallow/non-existent security is.

You would expect much more quality in an app from a giant like mc Donald's. offers are often empty and need you to quit the app, force stop it and go back in. credit card worked for a while but no longer. favorite restaurants are always forgotten. if you do not order from the closest restaurant, offers are not available. offers are not worth it most of the time, not as much as a year ago when the big Mac at 1$ was offered often. ok these were the problems, don't get me started about the interface
App freezes all the time. Reinstalled several times, still not working.

When I open the app it tells me that the version I have is no longer supported. it then automatically redirects me to my app store for an upgrade. McDonalds app doesn't have an upgrade available. This renders my McDonalds app useless. I tried uninstalling and reinstalling only to have the same problem come up. Don't abandon your app until you have the upgrade in place!
replyContent: Sorry for the inconvenience but this has been solved. Please try updating the app just in time to earn McCafe Mobile Rewards!

content: Free food got to love it. Did a mobile order and now the app is messed up can't do another mobile order with one outstanding and it keeps on saying I need to pick up my order I'm rather confused on what to do now with this problem

This is the most annoying app. Freezes all the time. When it works, there's a $50 order limit. My family of 5 can't keep it below that so I need to bring a second phone with a second order just to make this work for us. I found out you can't just bring the order # with you from the second phone (I left it home since we didn't think we needed it with order #).

App used to work fine. About 2 months ago it would make me sign in everytime I used it but it would just sit and load forever when trying to sign in. I've uninstalled/reinstalled about 4 times now. You would think that a company the size of McDonald's would be able to afford to get a wiring app made for them. Seems to me that it's on purpose.
This app doesn't work. I put all my items in the cart and it will not let me check out. I am so sad.
Why did you guys have to make changes? Now the app doesn't work anymore. I keep picking the closest McDonald's and it does a loop of having me pick the closest McDonald's.

This app does not save any time because the app takes long to browse through with badly designed menus. There's $2 small specialty coffee's right now on the menu and that isn't on the app. It's not in the offers, it's not anywhere. I searched the term "specialty coffee" like on the ad and it doesn't show up. Easy 1 star.

The app is useful as long as you can stay logged in. I used to stay logged in but lately I will be logged out from my account with the app hanging when I try to log back in. I have to uninstall and reinstall the entire app every time. Since the app is pretty much useless without being logged in, this is a serious problem. Please fix this issue. I have a Huawei P10.
replyContent: Hi there. We're sorry for the inconvenience and currently working on this issue. Please stay tuned for an update!

content: Lately I can't add a credit card to the payment methods. Which is absolutely needed for this app to function efficiently. It keeps saying, "an error occurred attempting to save your card. Please try again later". I've uninstalled and reinstalled the app, logging out and in, and making sure it's updated. Everytime I try and update I get the same error (over weeks). It's been 2 app updates and 1 OS update and the problem persists. Is there an ETA on fix?
replyContent: Hi Don, thank you for reaching out. This is an ongoing issue we are working very hard to resolve. Thank you for your patience as IT continues to look into this. Stay tuned for updates!

content: the app is great, easy to customize everything about your order. However you aren't really ordering ahead, since you have to be at the location before they even process your order. It doesn't actually save you any time. One other little annoyance is when you try to remove one slice of cheese from a burger that comes with two slices, you end up with no cheese every time because all it shows on the order is to remove cheese...
The app freezes all the time and half the time can't get the menus to open so just have to order at the speaker since app doesn't work.

It won't let me create an account for the app. It keeps redirecting me to keep sending it. My email that I used keep wanting to open but nothing. It was so hard to make one that I didn't even bother finishing it. Forcing me to confirm without letting me look around gave me a headache. It should be simple and have a an incentive to have but my first impression was bad. I will continue to use other apps instead of this one.

This app does not keep me logged in! Then when I try to log in again, I have to click "forgot password". A reset password email doesn't send instantly...instead it takes an hour to receive. I ended up getting 6 password reset emails as a result, all at once. I reset my password and it still fails to log me in...all I get is the jumping fries..why would I want to bother ordering off the app after going through this foolishness?
replyContent: Hi there. We're sorry for the inconvenience and currently working on this issue. Please stay tuned for an update!

content: Terrible App. When I first placed a mobile order, the order stuck on my account forever even though I had already gone to pick it up. I couldn't start a new order or somehow complete the order I already got. This is ridiculous..you shouldn't have to redownload the app everytime you place a mobile order. I tried closing the app, restarting it..nothing worked. I've never had this problem with any other app.

It doesn't work properly. I always have the same issue of not being able to redeem a coupon on the last day of it expiring. It says valid till 11:59pm but when I go to order my food just after 10pm on that last day the offer is already gone... they need to fix this issue immediately, I'm sure I'm not the only one who's pissed about this.....

My McD's has been historically the worst app I have ever used. But the latest version has just taken it to yet another level. I have not been able to load the weekly offer even for once for 6 straight weeks now. Indoor, outdoor, anywhere, you name it. With location turned on, offers would never show up. (Sometimes it would give me error code -1000). I am not even using a crappy phone (Samsung S9). And I am 100% sure my location service is fine (from the use of other apps). Please fix this !!!

What an incredibly broken garbage app. Has been difficult to use since the beginning, and now nearly impossible to get further than the starting screen before it bugs out and stops responding. I'm not exactly using an ancient phone. I guess McDonald's used the fast food of app developers to make this app for them... sloppily made with very little value. I was trying to order food, but since the app is so broken, I can't and therefore I won't. I guess I'll take my business elsewhere. Goodbye

Flat out doesn't work, won't even start up. Now that it starts up, it still is not functioning. The store was mystified when I showed up, as to who I was and what I was doing there. I am quite certain I paid for my breakfast twice because the store had very little interaction with the app that I submitted visa payment with. So I was forced to pay again and at this point they submitted my order to the kitchen to be made.
replyContent: Hi Jason, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email address, wifi or cellular connection, steps you took to get any errors, screenshots/error codes at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: This app is a good idea. I do end up at McDonald's more often because of coupons. It's just disappointing the app is so poorly built and appears to receive no testing before release. I don't understand why it's so hard to A) Log in B) Stay logged in. Every morning I reach the Drive Thru and order my coffee while wrestling with the login. Some days I reach the window before I can successfully log in and simply give up on that digital stamp.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for the feedback. Weâ€™ll use this info while we continue to evolve and improve the app. Stay tuned for updates!

content: Something that should be straight forward and useful that is rendered utterly obnoxious by being bogged down with unnecessary features. Constantly tells me not to use it while driving, I'm not. Demands I turn on Location. It doesn't need it. Has not once actually worked for me. Ugly, cluttered and janky interface. Stick to mailer coupons, they actually work as designed.

Managed to resolve a previous issue without the MCD reply, which is no help. I always have a very long delay before the app "sees" me inside the ordering location. On some locations it doesn't even even see me. 15 minutes go by and I'm still unable to buy my purchase. MCD reply bot: I DO have the latest version, I said I had to re-install the app in my previous edit. Did I not?
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. Please make sure you have the latest version of the app. If the issue persists please email ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: constant crashes. numerous error messages telling me to close and restart. sometimes that works, some times that doesn't. on my 5th reinstall. app was totally frozen today, no response. reinstalled.... still not responding. I still use this app A LOT it's handy when it's working, but the amount of times I go to use it and it doesn't let me order in a timely manner, is really just about got me ready to give up on McDonald's. please. I like your coffee SO much more than that other place. fix this
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email, type of phone, OS, app version, wifi or cell connection, and screenshots/error codes to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: Don't bother. The app routinely tells you offers that are currently active are not applicable or are unavailable. When you try to order breakfast at 8 am it will say that the restaurant is no longer serving breakfast. The number of errors in the app makes using it completely impractical. If you really want their food, just go in and order.

There doesn't seem to be much point to the app. The McDonald's in my area, is probably the slowest in existence. The only reason I downloaded the app was the hope that I could order ahead and not have to wait at the store for 20 minutes for 2 breakfast burritos. Not to be apparently. You have to be at the store to order. The wait to order isn't the problem with all the new technology. maybe you could look into this McDonald's? Thanks.

Very poor experience. Ordered and paid through the app and selected curbside pick up and entered spot number. Waited 20 minutes for the food and then went in to find out they did not get my order although the payment was already processed. Had to wait for the order to be made from scratch. Took a total of 35 minutes to get my order. And they were shorting he an oder of fries that I had to point out

Any time I want to use this app, I have to uninstall and reinstall it for it to work. Literally 5 times a week or so. It will not load past the login page, even when I know I have my login info correct. The offers are super valuable so it's worth it to me to keep uninstalling and reinstalling the app, but it's really annoying!
replyContent: Hi there. We're sorry for the inconvenience and currently working on this issue. Please stay tuned for an update!

content: This app needs to be crashed every time it is opened. The app will tell you there are deals to be had but you cannot access them. This thing glitches constantly. Every time I go to use this app I have nothing but problems. Update... after I was informed that the issues are fixed, the app works even worse than before. edit: the issues have not been resolved. the app is still glitching every time I try to ise it away from home.
replyContent: Hi there. Thank you for your feedback. This is an ongoing issue for some Android users that we are currently working to resolve. For the time being, a temporary fix is to uninstall and reinstall the app. Please stay tuned for updates.

content: This stopped working 2 update ago with payment issues. There is no way to add a new card, it gives an error that it can't be added at this time. This card used to work just fine in the same app. I was happy to see a new update but, same issue. Delete data and cache, same thing. The credit card I'm adding is valid, used to work and I use it almost daily. It's a shame that such a big company can't fix some basic issues like trying to give them money...

Absolute POS. Set everything up. Went to pick up an order and the phone told me there was something wrong with the payment. At that point, it would not let me leave the app no matter what I would do. It did, however, place my order (and charge me) two more times! Never was able to actually leave the app. Had to go to apps and force stop. Then clear memory. And then (of course) uninstall.  I don't like any app that will charge me 3 times for one thing.
App use to be good but once you switch phones it will not send you an email to verify your account. It's stupid. Gonna erase this app and never go back to McDonald's

What a nightmare, just order when you get there; app kept asking for me to ick loxation, even though it was on. Order did not get there GPS address was wrong. Order did not appear at location. They had to get order directly from me showing it to them. 15m later I got my order. Then order appeared on their system! ðŸ¤¡ Show! Will never use it again!

I had a credit card ðŸ’³ already registered from a while back, then I needed to switch my credit card. After deleting my card, I can't add my new credit card. I kept getting an error. I've reinstalled, cleared cache and data, even tried it on another phone, nothing seems to work. Is anyone even working on this app anymore? Seems like this is a problem based on other comments.

You prepay for your food but then have to check in at the McDonald's for them to start the order. This takes away all benefit of using the app. I can't believe that there was an executive who bonused off of creating an app that is nothing more than a terrible version of the Starbucks app. Corporate governance is obviously not strong with this company and they should just stick to being a real estate holding company.

Payment cards inexplicably started being declined. But at least I was able to check out and pay at the drive-thru. Then deleted the cards but was unable to add them back. Uninstalled and reinstalled 3x. Still unable to add CC. Now with no card added, I'm unable to checkout. Hence can't use the app. Prior to this problem, I was reasonably pleased with the app. Edit. I FOUND THE SOLUTION! The postal code must have a space. Somebody made a code change and did not tell anyone.

When this App is working, it's great, but there's problems every few months. THIS TIME - When I logged in,  it asked for the password, then it keeps saying the password is incorrect,I asked for the verification code to reset the password,  it keeps telling me the verification code is incorrect.  So frustrating......
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for sharing this with us. We are currently looking into this issue. We will be in touch soon!

content: Very poor app. You can be right at a McD's, connected to their own wifi be outside the building with a strong GPS signal and it will tell you that it can't find a store. Any type of system cleaner you use on your phone to clean trash files causes the app to require re installation to work, which means it's using the wrong file areas for file storage. While there may be some good deals on it, I uninstalled it, not worth the hassle. I just use other companies mobile ordering instead.

The app was working really well at first. For some reason, every time I open the app now it auto orders my last order when I don't even order anyting I literally just open the app to go use it. I've had to uninstall and reinstall the app just to place a single order lately. It's incredibly frustrating. And once it auto orders I can't actually order what I want because the app thinks I'm going to pick something up that I never wanted in the first place.
replyContent: Hi Krystle, thanks for bringing this to our attention. Please send us an email to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: Selected a restaurant not even near me when I ordered. Only saving grace is that it didn't charge me. One would think a company like McDonald's would be able to create a better performing app. Didn't even let me select the option to change restaurant location. The reason people use an app to order is to order ahead of time. What's the point in using an app if it's just going to give me the same experience as ordering in the restaurant, except less efficient?
The app works fine. But seriously, 25$ order limit? The guy on tv ads is taking an order for his whole family, there's no way it's under 25$.
Your app should stop asking me to check my wi-fries and wise up and function. My issue is not my wi-fi but the app itself.
You cant use the coupons half the time. Wont allow you to select any drink. By not allowing you to do so the order cannot be completed. Garbage app

App used to be ok. Then it stopped processing payments on the credit card that had been working fine. Cannot add new cards to my account. Always "an error when saving the card", regardless of the card or the time of day when adding. Uninstall / reinstall doesn't help. Defeats the purpose of mobile ordering when I have to go to the counter to pay - which would be fine, but no one acknowledges customers standing at the cash until you call out to the staff after waiting for sometime.

Can't do anything. The app freezes after it loads. Going off the main page then back again, it reloads but is still frozen. I don't have any screen control applications so I can't find any reason why it doesn't work. Then again, this app hasn't worked for me since 2017. When I upgraded my phone to a Samsung S9+ then a Pixel 3, it stopped working. I guess it only works with much older technology.
Cannot add payment method, so frustrating. A company as big as McDonald's must be surely able to develop an app that actually works.
Constantly freezes... It's the only app on my phone I have issues with.
Bad malfunctioning app! Tried to sign in but it won't let me because of the new format

The app worked well enough but this morning I can't get into it. I keep getting the message "Sorry this APP version is no longer supported. Please upgrade to the latest version available in your APP store." I've tried uninstalling, rebooting my phone and reinstalling the app with no change. Running a Note 5 on the latest Android OS.
replyContent: Hi there, we're so sorry for any inconvenience this has caused. We're happy to inform you that the issue on the app has now been resolved. Thanks for your patience.

content: This app is leaps and bounds ahead of all others like it, it's very easy to use and way convenient to use. Unfortunately when my credit card was updated and I tried entering the new number I'm unable to use the app at all. I've tried removing the old cards, logging out, uninstalling, and I even called customer support and they just told me they can't help me and to wait for the next update. Not much confidence in the backend of this app anymore.

Still having the same issue after 5 days! I can enter my order, but once I get to the final step to submit it to the kitchen, it won't work. Keeps saying I'm not connected to the internet, which I AM! And, when I line up to provide the cashier with my number so she can submit it, it won't allow my online transaction to go through. I was advised by you that this issue was fixed. Just thought you should know, it is definitely not.
replyContent: Hi Danie, thank you for getting in touch about your app experience. The error you were experiencing is an issue weâ€™ve been working on and have now resolved. Please restart your app.

content: Perpetual errors never end. Open the app, get an error; go to another card or pick a menu item, get an error; add a product to order, get an error; head to checkout, get an error. It works, but, boy oh boy, does it have quite the process to get there. Updated to add you don't get transaction numbers when ordering with the app, so if you need to contact McDonald's regarding an experience at a restaurant - you can't use their online form.

Worst app ever. The offers never load. Then they'll finally load but once I'm actually at McDonald's to use it, the barcode won't show up. It will keep saying error please try again. So at this point I'm already at McDonald's or in the drive thru so I just end up paying full price because the cashier won't accept the offer without scanning the barcode. My friend has an iPhone and her app always works. Definitely deleting this app

WARNING: Do not input credit card info! (Google "McDonald's Canada App Credit Card Leaks" to see why). When I first started, the app was great. The trouble started when I tried to take advantage of the Mobile Order/Curbside pickup option, which requires you to put in credit card info. All of a sudden, I notice I start getting charges from a random McD's in Vaudreuil, Quebec (I'm in Toronto), even when I'm not using the app or even in the country. McD's refuses to acknowledge the issue, despite all the other stories online that all share the same issue. They said "take it up with your credit card provider". In the end, I had to tell Amex to cancel charges as fraud, and get me a new card.
Useful app but the push notifications of coupons is not appreciated. Silenced the notifications. I hope regular use of the app doesn't need notifications to work

This application sucks. Too many issues. It's failed me numerous times when I try to order. Apparently I am not alone in experiencing difficulties with this app. My latest issue was today when I was trying to mobile order to avoid human contact but app wouldn't let me continue to complete my order. Ended up going into restaurant to find help with this app and staff acknowledged issues with app (again). Find real prof app developers so I don't have to risk my life to order big macs.

works fine. like having the in-store touch screen in your pocket. free coffee x2. Don't use the curb delivery. Ordering ahead doesn't appear to make anything faster. I reccomend it. I've also noticed that if anything goes wrong with my order I'll likely blame the app, but that may not necessarily be cause of the issue. However, if you can't enter the store due to renovations, you shouldn't be able to select a pick up from there.
replyContent: Hi there, we appreciate you taking the time to provide your feedback!

content: It is not a bad app but, when an error happens and a previous order is put through a second time, YOU SHOULD BE ABLE TO CANCEL THE ORDER. This is the first bug I ran into using this app. If an error occurs on the app, who developed it so that the order goes through anyway?! I am now stuck with an order that I didn't want to checkout with and I can't edit it to nothing to get rid of it. I am now unable to even order anything or update the order with anything else leaving the app useless.

Downgrading my review from 4 to 2 stars. The app itself, when it works, is awesome allows you to get your order ready ahead of time and then be super efficient when you get to the restaurant. The BIG issue here is that the app very regularly locks up on opening. Happens a few times per week, and when that happens, I often have to force stop and clear the cache for the app to get it to work. If that doesn't work, sometimes a phone reboot will do it, and in the case that doesn't, reinstall it.
replyContent: Hi there, thank you for taking the time to provide your feedback. We're sorry for any inconvenience this issue has caused and wanted to let you know that we're currently working on a solution. Please stay tuned for an app update!

content: Your app is terrible. First of all, it doesn't let me pick which location I want to pick it up from. There's more than one McDonald's close to my area and when I try to pick the location I want it still directs my order to a default. Second, there's always a problem with the offers. Please fix this! I really want to use the app more but its so frustrating.

I am updating my previous review rating from 4 to 1. For about 6 weeks, I have been trying to add a new credit card because the card on record has expired. Every attempt led to an error message that said " try again later". Without a stored payment method, the app becomes useless. Two emails and two phone calls to Customer Services finally resulted in an reply, suggesting me to wait for the next app update. This is unbelievable, as the app is not working and so much of my time has been wasted!
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for the feedback. Weâ€™ll use this info while we continue to evolve and improve the app. Stay tuned for updates!

content: Disappointing experience for an app from a company like McDonalds. I only use it for easy access to the discounts. It performs relatively poorly, and is slower than any other food ordering app on my phone. One of my biggest frustrations leading to only 2 of 5 stars, is because the app has allowed me to order to closed stores.

Overall experience is OK, I do get glitches such as not app shutting down or I get to payment and it freezes. But why do you not enable your 2 can dine coupons to be applied to an online order? In light of the external environment, it's annoying to have to go through a drive thru and explain you want to use the coupon when I could just add it to a mobile order ahead of time!!!

The app has 2 great features I use all the time: coupons and repeat order. However, the reason I gave it 2 stars is that it has some serious issues and design flaws. First, it occasionally doesn't allow you to order an item even though it's available at the restaurant. The other day I placed an order for 5 meals, but only 2 went through, so I had to go back to the restaurant and wait another 15 min to complete my order. Also, the order doesn't go through until you're physically at restaurant.
replyContent: Hi Tom, we appreciate you taking the time to provide your feedback as we can use it to continue to evolve and improve the app. Stay tuned for updates.

content: The app glitches most times, today I had my order ready to go and when I went to place it I got an error message that an item wasn't available. I proceeded to go in to the restaurant wait 20 minutes and got my desired order. Fix this....please.

content: Buyer beware... I have had this app for quite a while and loved it; but somehow last night two orders were successfully placed and picked up halfway across the country by someone else while I was asleep, and there is no way to report an issue with an order other than going to the store in question; nor is there a way to remove my method of payment from the app!
Cannot set up payment, no matter what I try. Seven different cards between two devices, and none work. Useless app if I can't set up payment.

This is one of the most incompetent and annoying apps out there. I need to log off and log in again almost every time I lauch the app; otherwise, it will just show me error 28300. content: This app drove me crazy. Many timesI was already in the restaurant but it kept saying I was not there even I clicked I was there. content: Not HORRIBLE, but for it being McDonalds, this app needs quite a bit of work if looking ti make things quick and convenient for clients.. Location doesn't update automatically (want something on the go? Wait 10 mins while your app tells you you're not actually at the closest mcdonalds before you place your order. And breakfast specials are frequently telling you it's the wrong time of day, even at 9:45am.

The app's been working like garbage lately. When I try to pick a location to pick up my order, most of the time the 'Save' bar at the bottom is faded out so i cant press it. This makes me totally unable to make an order. When it actually lets me pick a location, it doesn't let me check in to the store, even if im standing right in it. I think the point of mobile ordering is to save time, but im spending the same amount, if not more time reordering my stuff at the cashier or kiosk lately.

What is the point of this app? I can't order food unless I'm standing in the restaurant, even though you have my credit card? Then why wouldn't I just order it at the till? There is no time saved, and nothing is easier. Did anyone actually think these things out, or where you just so excited to have an app, that it doesn't matter if it is useful? Tim Hortons makes the food once it's paid for, and it's ready when the guest arrives. Superior app model.

App is total garbage. You cannot add PayPal, Interac, Debit Credit, or Google Pay as payment options, it's all strictly Credit Card only. Coupons won't load due to "experiencing problems" and this happens EVERY TIME YOU TAP THE APP. Quite honestly I have much better luck using Skip The Dishes. The "advice" they give on how to fix it is ineffective, too. App is uninstalled and company is no longer supported unless they start accepting responsibility for the app's continued dysfunctionality.

content: See I really liked the app at first, got good offers and whatnot on occasion. Recently it just stopped working though and I've seen other people with similar problems. Every time I open the app I had to login again despite clicking "remember me" every time and when i did login I got either, "can not connect to server" or "No offers right now, check again later" despite getting notifications from the app about the offers on at the moment. Tried uninstalling and reinstalling a couple times to no real avail, so just not really worth bothering anymore.

Then they tried to tell me that it was my credit card company that had to reverse THEIR charge...just called again and got nowhere and when I asked to speak to a supervisor was told "they all just left".
