content: There is literally no advantage to using this app that can't be accomplished by just going through drive thru or going inside. The app will allow you to place an order but will only start confirming and preparing the order once you arrive at the restaurant. The app actually tracks your GPS location so it won't start early no matter what. The entire usefulness of the app is to have the order ready or near ready upon arrival, otherwise what's the point?

Not very functional for ordering ahead, especially as compared to the Tim Hortons app. You can only "put your order through" once you arrive at the restaurant, which defeats the purpose of ordering ahead, since you are only then added to the queue and will still have to wait thr same amount of time for your food. Also, sometimes the app won't even recognize that you are at the restaurant and you will then have to wait in line for the cashier to help you enter the order.

Awful, huge install and very clunky navigation. Password requirement is ridiculous for such a simple function. The app absolutely requires location permission turned on not to crash in at least 3 different ways despite options available to look up a restaurant. Can't even use the app until permission changes, not even for nutritional look up or store look up. Awful awful app. Use a coupon then uninstall.

Won't log me in, just stays on the login screen after I type in my credentials. So much for the free soda. Seriously, more than double 1 ratings when compared to the others. The app is by far the worst food type app so many errors and nothing is really done to fix them. It's a real shame.

The deals aren't as good as they used to be now it's mostly for mobile ordering. I miss the $3 something any sandwich. I'd go get a big man or quarter pounder my kids would get happy meals. the mcCafe rewards used to work but now it doesn't. I don't care for this app anymore half the time I think I should just uninstall it already

Like the app. Still needs some work. For example, can not order a cup for a glass of water. Another problem is offers. Today I could have had a free cheeseburger with my order but I can not eat cheese on my burger. It would not let me remove cheese from the burger. So offer is unfair to me as I can not eat cheese and app will not allow me to remove it.
Stupid. Stop processing my cc and now I can't add any cc to it. It's keep saying "error, try again later"...

All the good coupons are now "Mobile order" only, and the mobile ordering is extremely broken. Items show up as unavailable for no reason after adding to the cart. Sometimes it just crashes when trying to open the cart; someone broke the cart activity starting. Loading times are atrocious. With all the errors and loading it takes about 30 minutes to order a meal for a family. Horrible, horrible experience.

Keeps signing me out. Then when you try to sign in it just sits there forever signing you in but doesn't actually sign you in. Uninstalled and reinstalled the app about 6 times in the past few weeks. Couple times that worked. Now it won't let me reset my password. Don't waste your time. It's Wednesday I'm going for whopper Wednesday. At least at bk I get it my way

Extremely poor and glitchy app. Always sends the order to the wrong store even when I'm standing with stone throws away from the store I want to order from. I tried putting through my complain via app and the online form cannot be submitted becuase it thinks I haven't selected the right province when I clearly did. Very poor design. Already lost two orders to a store I never go to. Will not recommend using this app.
App is only useful if you pre-order.. It was better when you could acces to discount from any method. Stopped going to Mcdonalds cuz of that ...its just not worth it anymore..

Like it, user friendly
I've had the app downloaded for about five minutes and have been fighting it to let me manually select my location. App deleted any minute now.

Bait and Switch! App offers mobile order offers to entice you then you get to the store and there's always a "technical problem" with the app. By this time you are already sitting at the restaurant in your car so you just go ahead with ordering without the mobile offers and paying regular price. This seems like the illegal practice of bait and Switch. I'll check with my lawyer buddies.

I have eaten elsewhere SOOO many times cause the app wouldn't even load enough to START placing an order. And why do I have to be in the parking lot to process my order? I like nuggets but they're always 15 minutes, why can't I place the order a few minutes early? Put an option in there to start early and it's on me if I take too long and it's cold.

worked the first time, failed the 2nd, and now the 3rd time it failed again when it came to sending my order to the kitchen. now I have an order stuck in limbo, and no one can tell me it is charged me or not, so possivpy double charged. This app sucks, has so many bugs. won't be using it again anytime soon.

I like the ability to pre order. Should show screen with how many steps left to order. I app ordered ahead, gave me code. When i go to the location, I went to check number on screen, not there. There were two more steps to finalize order. That was disappointing. But all in all, good app, with discount coupons save money.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. We'll use it to continue to evolve and improve the app. Stay tuned for updates.

content: Tried to make a order and the app didn't give me the option to pick it up inside the store or at the drive through then it said "sorry we are having some issues on our end" I gave the staff the order number and got nothing I was told to "try again" I have now been billed twice for a muffin that I never got and no longer want my app is still telling me to get my order and won't let me get past that point I'd like my money back for my order

Enjoyed the app until recently. Started with the order no being transmitted to the store, and being told to fiddle with my wifi settings at the drive thru window. Then been getting a fraud message for no reason and payments won't go through. Tried to change my credit card but app won't allow it, always giving an error message. Had to reinstall on my pixel3xl App has gone downhill severely.

Works fine. I pull up, get my food handed to me sometimes literally 30 seconds after my order is still an option with mobile delivery confirmation. Then i leave. Shave 10 minutes off of a dining experience..easily. I still don't understand why lining up in the drive thru is still an option with mobile ordering. When you can just go curbside close to the restaurant with no one around you why would you even think about getting in the drive thru after ordering your meal with your phone it's ridiculous
replyContent: Awesome! Thanks for the detailed review.  We're happy you're enjoying our offers and having a great Mobile Ordering experience.

content: What is the point of this app? I want to use it to save time, but it's impossible to place an order ahead of time, and pick it up in, say, 10 or 15 mins. The order is not complete and preparation of the order doesn't start until you choose how you'd like to pick it up (drive through, counter etc), but you can't choose the pick up method unless you're physically at the McDonald's location (app checks your location). It makes no sense really. Additionally, most locations are showing as closed.

I'm constantly having to log back into the app due to "Sorry, we're having some issues on our end. Please restart the app and try again. [error: -28300]". Its quite annoying as this process takes longer to do than to make my order! Other than that, I'm enjoying the app.
replyContent: Hi there. Thank you for your feedback. This is an ongoing issue for some Android users that we are currently working to resolve. For the time being, a temporary fix is to uninstall and reinstall the app. Please stay tuned for updates.

content: Very frustrating app to use, and is always lagging. Even more frustrating is that I forgot my password upon getting a new phone, so requested a new one. It asks for a verification code, and says to copy paste into the verification screen. Well, the app resets when you exit it, forcing you out of that screen, and there is literally no other way to try and reset it! Very frustrating, waste of time, and preordering is in no way faster than waking to the till.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for bringing this to our attention. Please send us an email to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: 2nd update and warning... DO NOT order extra jam or other condiments especially with breakfast. In my particular location I ordered jam in the app. The app charged me 15 cents for the condiment. When I approached the counter I noticed that the jam was not in the bag. I asked staff for the jam that I ordered and she said it would cost me 55 cents. I told her that I'd already paid for the condiment in the app but she still refused to give me the condiment unless I paid an extra 55 cents. I ended up paying the 55 cents so my extra jam ended up costing 70 cents in total. UPDATE: I ordered on the app. Got there and noticed that my order and one other were on the display board, mine was first. Another eight orders came in after my order. ALL of them were served before my order. I needed to get to work so i just told them to cancel the order. It was on the app so i will never see my $12.80. I just donated to a mega corporation.
replyContent: Hi Darren, we are sorry to hear this. We'd like to discuss this further, please give us a call at 1-888-424-4622 (Monday to Friday 9:00am-7:00pm EST, Saturday 10:00am-6:00pm EST) so we can further investigate.

content: Like what did you guys do? Now everytime I click 'select pickup option' it takes me to a blank screen with no options. It's safe to say that this app is broken now. At least on my Samsung S5 Neo. I guess that's too bad for Mcd's. I ended up just leavin' Mcd's and going down the street to grab something else. App deleted. Customer lost.
replyContent: Hi Tony, sorry for the inconvenience. We are aware of the issue and are working on it. Stay tuned for updates!

content: every time I try to order ahead I have had issues. stores losing my order. every single time it is faster to go into the store and pick up, rather than using the app. this last time, I ordered at a new store and it send the order to my default store. don't waste your time with this app.

Would be amazing if it didn't have so many glitches and bugs. Seriously, this app is an embarrassment to McDonald's software department. Obviously they're either underfunded, incompetent, or just don't care about their product. Maybe all three. The deals don't work half the time either. The real kicker is that this is the best food app I've seen, so maybe it's just the industry. FYI, currently all your drinks are invalid options on meal deals. Can you PLEASE get that fixed?!

All I want is to view the online coupons.  I was led by the web to install the app in order to see the coupons. The I run into th is super slow app which does not know how to handle network issue. After a long while it saids server down. In one of the attempt to click the see the ecoupon, the app ask me to select the province...then it drew contents from the coupon web site which ask me to select province again. At the end the app point me to install another McDonald's app.  All these confusing looping I still have not been able to see the coupons. Such terrible design.

Good grief this app has been abysmal since I downloaded it for the first time in 2017, resource heavy, unstable, and random login issues that happen every so often, where you can't even login to your account regardless of the quality of internet connection you're using, rendering the app completely useless. And to top it all off, now the offers you get just suck and aren't a good value outside of the free fries for McDonald's professional sports team sponsorships... This app needs a rebuild.

App did not work properly. Couldnt find my location. The store i went to pick up my order would only take QR code. App wouldnt give one. When i clicked order details it said the store was currenty closed. I was standing inside the store!! First and last time using this app. Developers should refine it more before releasing it. Wasted my time.

Do not order using this app unless your right next to the location, i placed an order in the app, thinking it was placed, i drove 20 min to the pickup McDonalds just to find out that the order is not processed until you arrive at the physical location, and it was too late and the items i ordered were no longer available, one of the worst app ordering experiences that i have ever had

Keeps telling me to update despite there not being an update. Wouldn't let me edit my card on file or add one (it had expired, got a new card with the same number and everytime I tried to add the card it would give me an error). Disappointed in that but it still let me order so I just paid in the restaurant. It's a straight forward app, wish the offers were laid out better but it's not terrible

This app is super slow & frustrating to use when I'm in a hurry which defeats the purpose of mobile ordering for convenience. You would think a big franchise like Macdonald's would create a efficient app but no... Buttons don't respond or freezes while loading. It should also add a feature asking for customer opinion/feedback after receiving the food order because I had a terrible customer experience at one location with a rude staff member regarding to my mobile order. She shouldn't work in front of house with that attitude of hers.

App never works correctly. Ive had it double my order (without showing me this on the final screen) ive also had it not add things i have had added to my order. I just got thr confirmation on the order and total and everything looked good , got my food and it was missing one of the meals and all of sudden its just not on the order and the amount charged is different. I took a screen shot of thr confirmation so i know its not my error.

the app is a great way to go... don't need to bring your wallet can see what custom options are available and customize easily the offers on the app are unique and frequent! when McDonald's has coupons out, you can find them in the app too. ("coupons" is not the same as "offers") one can really explore the menu the app is specific to the McDonald's location you're at, so some McDonald's that have special deals will show up in the app too. sometimes a bit slow to load. pretty stable.
replyContent: Hi Mister T, thank you for  your review! We're happy to hear that you are enjoying our mobile app.

content: The app works great however the restaurants are not properly staffed to handle the mobile orders. They never have them ready when using the drive through. If you request table service they just don't have the staff to bring the food promptly. Eventually maybe they will get it more streamlined but so far it takes longer using the app
replyContent: Hi Sheldon, thanks for your feedback. Please try following these steps: log out of your My McD's account, clear app cache, uninstall and reinstall the app, restart your device and log in back again. If you're still experiencing issues please send an email to ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: Earlier versions of this app were stable and it was useful for me to keep my McCafe bonuses and order ahead and get their mobile discounts. Since about October 2019, it is very unreliable; most of the time it just gets stuck a few seconds after opening to the home screen. Very frustrating!

still no fix for android users for mobile offers, which has taken way too long for a multinational company to fix. uninstalling and reinstalling an app is not a fix. also annoying to receive email offers that say are available only through the app but the app isn't fixed to receive the offers. makes for a very poor customer experience.

Problem 1: Password length limit, more than 8 characters but less than 12. You want bad passwords? This is how you get bad passwords. 2. If you forget the password, and then try to change it, you need to enter a verification code that's emailed to you. When you switch to your email app for the code and switch back to the app, it will move away from the password rest screen. Dumpster fire/10 guys.

Terrible app. App is clunky and not user friendly. Constantly experiencing difficulties so order wont go through. Only way to fix is to re-install and you lose your profile and have to reset up. App changes location for no reason and order is not there when you get to the restaurant. Good luck getting a refund. They expect you to dispute charge with your credit card company which mine refused to do and never did get resolution from McDs.

App doesn't work Hafe the time. App will open but won't load the page or load the deals 90% of the time. On the odd time that you can open the page there's always issues with the Coupon itself so it won't work. The deals aren't that awesome either so the app isn't worth it. The coupon book you get in the mail is better than this app. Not worth it.
replyContent: Hi Sarah, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email address, wifi or cellular connection, steps you took to get any errors, screenshots/error codes at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.ï»¿

content: i used the app today and now it doesn't work is so frustrating because some deals are only available online and 9 times out of 10 it didn't load offers McDonald's should be ashamed of themselves...Tim Hortons app always works great did i say ALWAYS. McDonald's app is either it's having technical difficulties or the restaurant doesn't support the offers ( it actually does) or no matching offers found what a joke from the works largest QSR chain.
replyContent: Sorry for the inconvenience but this has been solved. Please try updating the app just in time to earn McCafe Mobile Rewards!

content: Used app to order. Checked in at correct store. Waited 15 minutes went in told order payment wasn't processed. Verified order address and items on app with employee. Showed email it was paid for. They said okay waited in lobby for a few minutes then said can I wait in my vehicle and someone will bring my order. Yes. Checked my bank account. Order charged. After 30 minutes went back in showed email and bank info. Got food that had been sitting under hot lamps. No apology. Later found app had sent payment to another location. Not my fault and they should have picked that up in the email I showed them. Will never use this app again. Uninstalled!

STUPID APP!!! It never just works. I get notifications about McDonald's specials and can NEVER get into the app to use it. Like I mean NEVER. The app always brings up the error message saying "WE ARE HAVING TECHNICAL DIFFICULTIES. TRY BACK LATER". Problem is though, the error message never gies away and I can never use the app.

Horrible app. It has gotten worse than it used to be. And it was bad before (before the stupid jumping arches ordering animation). Biggest issue: SLOW. Load menu? Slow Load previous order? Slow Load favourite? Slow Want to pick up your order? Can't do that until the app decides you are close enough. I want to time my order with when I get in the line. That's the whole point of this. Bring back the I'm here button. Whoever programmed this needs to learn software development
replyContent: Hi, thanks for the comment! Please make sure you've updated to the latest version of the app. We've now added a new 'I'm Already Here' button so you can choose your pick-up method and we'll start preparing your order earlier.

content: This is a stupid mcdonalds app. You sign in to put in codes and it tells you that your not signed in. What if you bought mcdonalds and you got codes to put in but it doesn't work. Help.

I used the app every day. While at a drive through I was told, "it didn't go through". I paid with another card. It turns out both went through. I was robbed of $14.88, and the only restitution is two coupons only good at McDonald's. My money was good anywhere, now it's only good at McDonald's . Customer Service, awesome, great people. Your policies governing the app and your stealing of people's hard earned money needs to be amended immediately.

App malfunctions so many times when need it to work. go to mcd just bc of offer and then app malfunctions...continuous bouncing french fry that never loads offer, offers malfunctioning ("oops something went wrong"), not able to sign in, etc. frustrating...time waster, $ waster (as pay more than intended, if don't leave empty handed). good app when works as intended. also, should be allowed to use 2 offers with Habs free french fries offer, then McD would make some money w those there to save $.

Horrible app for a multinational like McDonald's. A bunch of issues. -Have to clear my cache evertime I use it or else I get an error. -Big ad to announce 1$ coffee buy still 2$ when you add to order... - If you want to get your free coffee from the app reward promotion, you can't pay an upcharge to get a larger coffee - If you order from a previous order in your history, it charges you the same price as your previous order even if an item of your order is cheaper/on special.

Had this app. Tried using several times. never served up one deal. Always an error retrieving. Wasted my time trying to get their deals. Thoroughly disappointing experience.... A competotor has a much easier experience. Just login and get the coupon you select. Not sure what McDonald's was trying to achieve but so far not hitting their whole market with this app!

Offers me deals that are not always current. I check the app at home for deals, then go to the restaurant and open the app again and the deals have changed. EDIT: June 21- App has been working great for quite some time now. I enjoy it now. I almost always use the app for ordering, and utilize a deal they have going. It's a must have app if you frequent McDonalds. I changed the star rating from 3 to 5 stars.

One of the worst apps I have ever seen! extremely unreliable. constant crashes. opening a notification lands on a broken offer page "always" saying no matching offers now or nearby. orders cart cannot get empty so when the coupon code expires in the cart, you always see an error going there, and yet you cannot delete items! McDonald's instead of wasting money on promoting mobile app, giving free fries and stuff you should spend few bucks fixing your app! both Android and iOS apps are terrible

The app has completely stopped functioning. I will open it and it is frozen in place, there is no possibility of navigation. This is not an issue with my phone, as all other apps/functionality are fine. Not sure what happened here, as I used to love doing curbside orders but am now completely unable to even look at the menu.

This app started out great, but now recent orders or favorites never load. It's just faster to order from the crew. Which I'm pretty sure is the opposite if what this app was intended for. I keep checking back in hopes it has been fixed, but it's been months. Great idea terrible app. A shame.

Had to delete finally. Was fine for the first month or so and then after that the offers wouldn't show up on the app unless I was in town but not where I live in the outskirts. Not handy if I was planning lunch when heading in. The last straw was two times on different days I was actually in the restaurant and the app said there were no locations nearby and suggested I change my search criteria or postal code. I had earned a free coffee on the app and couldn't use it!

every time I want to claim an offer it always gives me an error. I have to uninstall then reinstall the app again on .y phone. this has happened with two other friends as well. now it's given me another error and it won't even let me view the offers. very frustrated with this, please fix these issues.

Great app, take the order from home and they get our order once arrived and it's already paid. Also, we can chose how to get our order. We have everything on the menu and extra deals only on app. However, i hate that we cant get the offers from the website on the app so we cant use this mobile app. For example, 2 trios for 11$. Also, when we arrive to take out, we need to take our phone to tell that we are here, select drive threw, and take number, really isnt ideal when driving...

The app is good when it works, however it is very buggy. My credit card expired and i am currently unable to add a new payment method...tells me to try again later. So now I'm unable to use the app for payment. Error messages are general and I'm often wondering why I can't get to the next page. Difficult to remove offers in the cart if you want to swap one for another, and there are issues using lunch offers before 11am, even though the app allows lunch orders pre 11am. The app needs improving.

The reason I use app is to save time. But this app will not submit your order until you walk into the place. It tracks your location with your phone gps. So you still end up waiting 5-10 mins. Starbucks app is 100% better, they should attempt to do something similar.
Works well 95% of the time. Wish they would add tartar sauce on the side like they do with mac sauce.

Terrible experience! If your products are not available then do not let a customer order them only to have them go to you location to be disappointed. Ordered, went to location to pick up and was advised that 5 of my 7 items were not available. Offered substitutions for same price but lower value, Requested a refund, was told to do it in my app. There was not option in app as I had already paid. Had to wait while manager called around to figure out how to refund me. Frustration/dissatisfaction

Keeps crashing when you first open it. Almost like it can't finish loading. perhaps it's an older bug they haven't yet addressed. Other than that it's pretty useful. Would also love it if they kept location off but it stays on for quite a while. Not a major issue, but just something to be aware of!
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for your feedback. Please send us an email with your login email address, wifi or cellular connection, steps you took to get any errors, screenshots/error codes at ca-appfeedback@ca.mcd.com so we can help.

content: Honestly, I didn't expect such a weak app from McD. As if this app could be any worse. content: Not starting your order until you check-in @ the restaurant causes unnecessary delays, why not use a Starbucks format and encourage mobile orders to be a quick hand-off? The expedience of a mobile ordering platform is negated when you don't even start the order until you've spoken to the attendant @ the speaker (who would have initiated your order anyway). My previous order is never cleared prior to starting new transaction, reboots are often required.

I can't believe there is no way for me to cancel an order on the app. I called customer service and they told me to uninstall the app and wait 24 hours for the order to cancel itself and reinstall the app. I can't believe that a company is largest McDonald's either completely missed this huge flaw in their app or are just trying to trap people into having to pay for an order they no longer want or need.

uninstalled the app as it was asking for an updated version. did that and got the same results with no link or info on an update. Also I cant say I'm particularly happy about having to pay for a condiment for my fries. its not like we, as customers, aren't already paying a lot of money for our meals but now we have to pay for basic stuff to go with our meals. Next thing you know McDonald's will be charging us for parking, salt, napkins...perhaps a coin operated washroom?...thx McDonald's!
Love it all time!!!!

It crashes often especially the last 2 weeks..... I liked this app..... Not anymore...... it crashes every day especially when there's free fries the day after a the habs score the first goal promotion...... it's frustrating and annoying...... what are the McDevelopers are doing with this app!!!!.... they forgot to repair the glitch....... it's been for months now!!!!

content: Definitely was not tested thoroughly. I have issues with this app on an almost daily basis. Today myself and another user had the same order #. Yesterday the app couldn't pickup my location. A handful of other times the app is having technical issues and can't be used. Also what's the point of adding a favourite location if you can't choose it from a list. content: While I enjoy the convenience the app should be giving me, there's a lot of flaws. Payment is always rejected, saying my card is fraudulent, but I use the same card to pay at the window. You also can't customize items in trios, such as replacing cream with milk in iced coffees part of meal deals, rendering those coupons useless if I want to have the meal my way instead of the default.

Eats up battery power, most likely from location permission. I turn of all permissions, only turning on location when I use the app. The invasion of privacy versus any perceived benefit for keeping the app active and rooting through the phone just isn't worthwhile. I even select 'force stop' after using it. It's slow and misbehaves. If you tell it what Province (for the coupons), you will have to tell it again upon leaving the page and going back to it even if you haven't closed the app. Fix it.

always have to have ur location services on. I want to choose my restaurant without having to enable my location services. can't do anything until I enable my location services. app is slow. no matter how often I save a favorite restaurant it never remembers them. When I try to access the feature of scanning a promotion at restaurant it always says "something went wrong please try again."

Just spent 15 minutes trying to log it. App took 2 minutes to tell me password was wrong. Took 3 minutes to say my email is already in use. Then sent me "verification code" but email came with temporary password instead. Said "copy and paste temporary code" but app does not let you paste anything in password. After typing temporary it took at least 3 minutes to say it is not the code - for pit sakes! The worst app i've ever used! Got me so mad I even came to complain about it! How does a multibillion dollar empire of a company can't make an app that people do not hate!?!?!

I ordered for curbside pickup with my baby in the backseat using the app. When I arrived, I notified the staff that I was in the parking spot. Then my order showed completed on the app even though I never received it. App has no way of notifying the staff that order wasn't received. Only way to dispute is to get out of the car which defeats the purpose of curbside pickup and I was unable to do so with my sleeping baby. I waited almost 20 minutes and left without getting my order. Terrible design

content: For previous version. Will wait and see.

content: Crashes more often than not, extremely slow and unresponsive, far too heavy for what it's supposed to be. Weirdly slavish to WiFi-based location, which is a problem when you're a commuter and the app insists that you're actually 20 minutes away at a different transit station because that's where the Wifi is centralized out of.  The app apparently has a feature that saves your favourite store. It never works. Despite using it for the same location every single time, it never remembers this, and instead tries to send me to McD's by the station 20 minutes away. I'm using the same restaurant everyday, it's not hard to make an app figure this out... and yet here we are.  Just a really badly built app. Whomever McD's subcontracted to build this should be replaced with a more competent app developer because there's no way an app from a billion dollar corporation should be built on what seems like a shoestring budget. This feels like it was subcontracted out to overseas "developers".   How is it that small chains can build much better and more functional apps with customer-friendly features than an international powerhouse like this?
Trapped in an endless loop of being told to log in, needing to resend the email but then it says email is already verified. I gave up and uninstalled.

This app rarely works and is super glitchy. You have to sign in to the app every single time you want to use it and it more often than not it gives sign in errors and asks you to restart but that still doesn't fix the problem. Not worth downloading till they fix all the issues. Waste of time.

content: Kind of surprised how glitchy it is. Don't work all the time.

content: I like the app, but it's really frustrating to force close it on Android each time that I want to see the offers. If I open it the first time, it'll show no offers available, but as soon as I reset it, it all shows up. I figured the latest updates would have fixed this by now.

content: Summary: Sends Order Only Once In the Store (Dumb!) The McD's user interface is great, it is quite clean. However, it does not deliver on its primary purpose... Convenience! The critical flaw is the app does not send the order to the kitchen until you ar physicslly at the restaurant location, within metres/feet. This effectively means it takes the same amount of time to just walk in and order on touchscreens, or use the drive through. So pointless!!

Sometimes it works. Sometimes it doesn't. Crew members at the restaurant don't know how to cope when the app doesn't work. Forget about any markdowns in prices if your app doesn't work, even though the app appears to clearly be working. You also can't cancel an order or add to it once you're past the drive through area. I'm not sure if the savings are worth the hassle tbh

Downloaded it so i could order food in a McD's while waiting outside (my car was in the shop). The app said that everything in this particular 24hr location was completely out of stock. between myself and another gentleman doing much the same thing (the location was near several auto dealerships) neither of us could get it to allow us to order anything. The locations employees suggested be use uber eats. =/

HORRENDUS. If you want to use the offers, you have no choice but to delete the app and reinstall it EVERY TIME. Why? Because you need to login which wouldnt be a problem if the fries didnt keep jumping forever. Have to reinstall every few weeks to get it to not be ridiculously slow. It also refuses to remember my favorites, I set them up and the next time I go to order the favorites list is empty again.

When I check the email I have to switch apps, then I need a new email to recover the password. one more glitch in a very weak app. UPDATE: HAD TO REINSTALL THE APP, NOT WORKING ANYMORE, NOW IM RECEIVING SPAM EMAIL TO MY 2 EMAIL ACCOUNTS AND CAN'T USE THE APP. WENT TO A RESTAURANT AND THEY WON'T HONOR ANY OFFER WITHOUT THE APP. HONESTLY, RIDICULOUS!!! UNINSTALLING IT FOREVER.

Try to reinstall and forgot password, when I asked to reset password and got the confirmation code, when you go back to the app it resets and you can no longer use that confirmation code and have to ask for a new confirmation code. Vicious circle.

App was working well for the longest time. Recently payments stopped working. First it happened 3 times in Toronto. So I thought it was a Toronto issue as it was working at home. Went home and payments stopped working here too. Tried clearing cache and data. Nothing. Uninstalled and reinstalled nothing. Signed into my daughters account and then back into mine, nothing. Removed payment cards and tried re adding them now it won't let me add them back in. Frustrated.

No order cancel button. After dismissing a notification about a deal, I got a new notification saying my order would be ready for pick up at a nearby store. It was an order I placed last week through the app that had somehow reordered itself. There is no way to cancel an order. I called the customer service line and pressed '3' for app issues, and there is nothing they can do but "write a report"... how inconceivable could the notion of a cancel button be for creators of an app that makes purchases?

first time using this app to order food and it triple charged me. basically no help from the company after I called them that same day. this is a 'good' app if they want to lose customers due to multiple problems and lack of customers service in resolving the problems.

Do not and I repeat DO NOT give McDonald's your credit card number. I was scammed out of $27.11 likely by one of their own employees who changed my pending incomplete single breakfast sandwich mobile order. An insanely frustrating experience and they were no help at all. Had no access to my credit card number as I had to put through a fraud investigation. I'm still having to update everything. Really infuriating. Has happened to a lot of people and who knows how many others that don't notice it.
replyContent: Hi Rob, we are sorry to hear this. We'd like to discuss this further, please give us a call at 1-888-424-4622 (Monday to Friday 9:00am-7:00pm EST, Saturday 10:00am-6:00pm EST) so we can further investigate.

content: Paper coupons cannot be used in app. I used the pickup option for the first time and it was unclear if I could schedule the pickup. There is no scheduling. The deals in the app are not very good. The food came out hot and didn't take very long. This is the third time I've installed this app since it's not easy to use, I may delete again since it hasn't improved very much.

Overall a good app, but missing a few things. You can only order small or medium iced coffee but they sell large ones - why can't you order all sizes? Also with an iced vanilla coffee you can extra syrup but can't order with half sweet (light on the syrup). It would be nice to be able to leave custom instructions or make a half flavor portion an option.

The mobile offers seldom work, and placed orders tend to disappear upon arrival at drive-thru. Moreover, if you're charged for an order that doesn't appear from a cashier's system then McDonald's remediation policy is to have you, the customer, present a bank statement indicating proof-of-purchase. I would not recommend mobile ordering until they've ironed out their bugs over the next decade.

A very easy to use app. I love being able to customize my orders in every way. Other restaurants online apps do not allow the same amount of order customization. Having several food allergies and sensitivities in our family being able to customize is greatly appreciated. Doing curbside pickup with the app and teacking my McCafe 'points' on the app is golden.

The screen just freeze on me like all the time when I open it. My phone is working perfectly fine. Edit: it kept denying my credit card for no reason. Even when I got to the place and use the same credit card to pay with 0 issues. Deleted my card, can't add it back. Giving me the try again later error.

Twice now I've used the app and have gone through the drive-through only to be told that they don't have my order, despite the app giving me a confirmation code. Very frustrating, especially when you use mobile only deals that they will not honor when you try ordering there.

The app is great when it works, but it often just says "error" when you try and redeem coupons. i find it incredible that one of the world's biggest corporations can only get their app to work half the time. I would give one star, but it technically has worked in the past.

Offers do not load frequently. Suggestion to re-install app does fix the issue temporarily, but everytime the app does not load means uninstalling and reinstalling which is not practical for android users. Also it is a reoccurring issue, we cannot be expected to do this every single time to get offers to load.

replyContent: Hi there- we are here to help! Please contact our support team at (833)-778-2929, or by email at appfeedback@subway.com. Have your app version, device type, and the steps to reproduce any errors ready- so we can investigate and address these concerns for you. Thank You!

I tried to use the app. I really did. The animations were cute, the ordering was straightforward. I created an account. I added a payment method (credit card). I tried one of the offers (free fries with burger). I picked a location to pick up. I went to pay and. Nothing. "Your payment did not go through, try another payment method.". I tried again, same problem. I deleted the card, re-entered it in case it was incorrect. Still would not go through. I though that perhaps that although the location I was ordering listed mobile payment as available, they do not accept my particular credit card at that location. So I tried to purchase a digital wallet credit through the app. This worked. I bought a $10 credit, no problems. So I re-order and choose Digital Wallet as the payment method. "Your payment did not go through, try a different payment method.". I tried ordering through the web site, same error message. I checked my email, maybe I had forgotten to validate my email address. Nope, still won't work. At this point I'm BEYOND DONE. A few days later I happen to be by a Wendy's location so I go in store to at least try and use the digital wallet credit. In the end I was able to do so, though apparently this option is used so infrequently that no-one at the location except the manager knew how to actually use it. This app fails in the absolutely most basic level. If you can't actually complete an order it's useless and a waste of everyone's time, and all it does is expose users to potential for data breaches and privacy violations. After I used the one time code from the app I deleted my payment methods and uninstalled the app. When I described the problem to the manager of the Wendy's location, his response was "Yeah, I gave up on the app a long time ago.".

replyContent: So sorry to hear you've had issues with our latest update! Lettuce wrap is still an option, and you can swap your bun for lettuce wrap by tapping on the bun under What's On It and selecting lettuce wrap. replyContent: So sorry to hear you had issues with the offer! Please make sure the offer is in your bag, along two a la carte Dave's Singles. Horrible. It navigates smoothly but it doesnt do as it is advertised. Also when my local wendys does Uber Eats, I have to call and remind them to sticker/staple my order when that should be STANDARD. When trying to order through the app, for example today, there's a promotion for a free homestyle chicken sandwich with any order through the 8th of November. When I tried to place my order, there was nothing showing the chicken promo was added or even existed afterwards (have the screenshots)
The app stops working every time you get in the drive thru. 4 times now. 4. It just loads forever. You leave? Instantly works. Don't install it.

"free chicken sandwich" wouldn't scan even though I had a purchase with it. Took forever before the manager finally just screw the app and gave me the sandwich for free without it. Probably won't be using this again and you've probably lost me as a customer for a really long time. Same thing happened to me with Burger King's app with "free" offers. These fast food companies really need to realize these things piss people off more to the point you will lose more money.

Does not work well. While in the drive through, i have had my coupon clipped and ready to go. The clerks then couldn't scan. Thus you pay full price. Even if you order for mobile pick up the food still isnt ready. Workers don't seem properly trained on using the app either, and i doubt that it's their fault.

Man cash is king yo... I have cash I cannot use this cause there is no option and now I will never even stop through the drive through. I am sick of this one world currency thing that's happening with basic stuff like this. No more wendy's for me simply cause I know things won't change over my individual opinion about wanting to use cash with the app... I want things delivered yo... What's so hard to figure out about this... You're millionaires and I'm poor as hell & cant use what little I have.
It could use a bit more. Like requesting salt packets or ketchup packets. Also, it is lent. The fish sandwich should be available on the app.

The app is good enough, it gets the job done, and I so much more enjoy ordering food this way rather than trying to tell my order to a drive-thru microphone. They've hid the Offers under the Rewards portion of things, so it's a click or two harder to find them. My real problem with the app is needing to enter my credit card's CVV *every time* I place my order. No other app has me do that, and I hate trying to have my card on me, and have to pull it out to look at the back each time.
The app symbol continues appearing in my phone tab, meaning the app is still active, even after completing my order and closing the app. It drains my battery, forcing me to reset the app permissions.
This App is nothing but trouble! Does not open on a continuous basis. Can't scan for points when the stupid thing won't open.

App will not process payments. Let's me place my order, and has nice exclusive deals. These facts are useless when you can't actually place the order. I tried multiple cards that all had triple the amount my order should cost and repeatedly tells me it can't process my payment.

I like that they have built in a Rewards system into the app, however the app has a few issues. One problem is it lists food items such a Coke Zero that are not available at the restaurant. Why would you list a food item that is not available? The offers section is very problematic. I've tried several times to claim the offer for free pub fries, but no matter what I do it says I need to add additional food items to my cart. I really wish they would fix it.
I have had an issue with the password reset multiple times. Entered the correct email for it and still have an error message. There has to be a fix to this

The app is pretty easy to use and great that mobile orders automatically earn the rewards. Downsides are plenty: You have to show the app in order to gain points, you can only have one card stored and the mobile ordering extremely lousy. Several times I have placed mobile pick up orders and they are never ready. They also take longer than if you were just to order in the drive-thru, making this option useless. What's the point of it when you end up having to get out of the car to get your order?
Unfortunately, what I thought to be a solid app is actually broken. Don't tell me I can place a breakfast order until 10:25 and then lock me out at 10:23.

Error Code 0201-4 I love Wendy's and I love the App deals. But, I keep getting this error code 0201-4 on the checkout screen. I've tried logging out and reinstalling, nothing seems to work. Unfortunately, you have lost me as a customer until this issue gets resolved. I've been visiting the second best for going on three weeks now, Whataburger. Please contact me, I miss my Wendy's burgers.
Not Useful for store near me. The store requires pick up through the drive thru. This saves no time, and you might as well wait in line.

Good but don't go on Friday or the weekends. Orders take over a half hour to fill and the line keeps growing and growing. I had no problem with the app, make sure your location is on. Most people are having problems probably don't have their locations on it. The offers or not that good anymore, I only go there because I love the food. I got a free chili last night with my points. For that, the app is worth it. I wish we get more points for our orders though.

And another horrible fast food app. I tried to order a salad, no dressing. Seems simple, right? Except I can't - no dressing is an option, but I had to pick TWO, and no dressing only counts as one option. So, couldn't order my salad, another uninstall. There clearly is NO QC on these apps. Errors like this should not be possible with a company that tried even a little bit.
Overall a good app. The only problem I have is with order notifications. They don't clear out through normal means, I have to open the app.
Absolute garbage app. Tried to use it to to scan coupons but I don't even see the option. Ended up going to another local restaurant. Will never use the app again

App used to work pretty well, but ever since they added the whole "rewards points" thing, it's been a mess. The process of getting a "reward" is less intuitive than the original way of getting an offer, and I haven't been able to successfully claim a "reward" or even make a regular order - I can't get through the checkout. All I get at that point is "oops, something went wrong," which isn't very helpful. Also, there's absolutely no way to change my misspelled name on my account.

There are so many issues with this app. The biggest one is the user interface which isn't intuitive and very inconsistent. Hire someone who does UI design to fix it. Second, I couldn't choose a payment method at checkout. The payment section was disabled and I intermittently got an error 0201-500 when going to the shopping cart. Lastly, when I ordered in a Wendy's and tried to use an offer that I loaded to my QR rewards code, it didn't work. The cashier tried to scan it multiple times.

Logged in, took 3 tries since it made me redo it without registering. Using the pickup/carry out option, I ordered (1) 4 for 5 crispy chicken sandwich combo & 3 cookies. I clicked the I'm here button to start making my order. I get there 10 min later and nothing is made. Only then did I see I was charged for and given (2) combos, she gave me 2 cookies instead of 3 like I ordered and paid for. When I called, she was rude and dismissive as if it's not her problem because I used the app. Just wow.

Like most mobile apps, this one needs a lot of work. I paid for my order and headed to the restaurant. When I got there, they did not have my order. I checked my bank account and the app had charged my card, then immediately refunded my card. And the app put everything back in my bag. So I am still hungry. Deleting the app now.
App seem to can't find my location. I'm in the Wendy's parking lot and it's showing me another Wendy's 3 miles away. Had it before and it worked pretty good now I'm not sure
Come on! Fix your App! Your offers don't load up. You drive all the way to the resturant only to find the offer doesn't load. ðŸ‘ŽðŸ‘ŽðŸ‘ŽðŸ‘ŽðŸ‘Ž

This app is ridiculous. When you load offers and rewards onto your card, they are not recognized at the store. When you attempt to place a mobile order, it charges your card but then gives an error that it can't complete your order. Wendy's is my go-to place but when the on-site manager refuses to help or take the item off even with proof, makes me want to never go back. Fix it!

The app is okay. I like how theres offers you can use but for the checkout portion needs improving. I got a Wendy's giftcard from a friend so I loaded it to my account and used it fine but when you have like 5$ left and your order is more than that then you have to load more money into your account to use it. It doesnt let you use your gift card and a credit card at the same time. You either have to add more funds to the account or just pay with your card which is really annoying.

I loved this app when I first installed it and started using it. It worked great! I had my QR code scanned both in store and in drive thru to get my points. I even had enough to redeem for a couple of free items. About two weeks ago, when I would try to have code scanned it would show error "failed to get customer QR code". I thought okay, something's wrong with the app, or my phone I restarted my phone, still get error msg. I uninstalled app and reinstalled it, same problem. Awful!
Delivery address can't put apt/unit number?
Its good,but the app should have ALL the drinks that are in the machine, for example when you click on a sprite it should bring up the different flavors.

It's great for coupons and for the rewards. However I learned the hard way that if you put your giftcard into the application you have to have the exact amount of your order. You can't use a giftcard for part of an order and cash for the rest. My restaurant can't scan the application to pay. Not all of the franchisees have the ability to use all the features of the application.
It uses a persistent notification to spy on your location a day or more later. You can check it by killing the location permission and all the sudden the persistent notification goes away.

I found this app to be a bit disappointing from the start and even more so with their new rewards added. In order to use the rewards you either have to use in the app or have it scanned in the restaurant. This is more problematic when I'm going through the drive-thru and using my phone for navigation or other purposes. plus they always have deals at the restaurant that are better than anything I find in the app. Others allow me to enter a receipt after the purchase. This one does not.

Update: 10/27: I was told by employees at 2 seperate locations that their scanners do not work, therefore you will not receive any points and there is a chance they will decline your offer/coupon at the window because its "unscannable". This app is definitely tailored for mobile orders, it seems like nothing is actually useable in-store. ZERO STARS IF I COULD! New "rewards" system is absolutely terrible. i've scanned three times in the last week and haven't received a single point

The app works great for mobile orders. However, if I try to scan the app at the window, it never works. I've now twice paid for items that were supposed to come off as "deals" (at 2 seperate locations), and I've yet to gain any points from scanning. I even sent in my receipt to request points be added but they never were. In the app, I wish it would give more customization options for sauces and freestyle drinks, and I hate typing in the cvv every time, what's the point of saving my card?!.
App is garbage now and, pushes order-ahead insanely hard and is very dependent on a stupid "rewards" program. Yeah, 2005 called and said it wants its loyalty cards back.
replyContent: Sorry to see this.  Can you call or text us at 888-624-8140 so we can get this addressed?  Thanks!

content: Refuses to complete ordering process. Tried to order, reinstalled... Ordered McDonald's instead. Your buggy app cost you a sale, hope that's what you're looking for

Can't figure out out to take advantage of the free breakfast baconater ended up spending 15 minutes in the app to just cancle and go to the store and was late to work playing with the app no advantage of placing your order on the app other than reward points they don't make your food till your there anyway

Bad Experience from start. Time after time I attempt to place an order the app had to restart. Once i get to placing my order and ready to pay, I am asked for the CVS code every time, not a great design. How often does someone have access to the credit cards when using the app. No other payment options.

Wendy's app circumvents my location tracking permissions by using a persistent notification that does not go away until i reboot my phone, this is a serious privacy issue that is unacceptable no matter what the service is.

I like that I can order my food before getting to the drive thru but I don't like the fact that the only choice of tea is unsweetened. I drink half sweet/half unsweetened and my husband drinks sweet tea. We have to tell them at the order speaker and they still give us unsweetened

This app has a LOT of issues. Crashes & closes out every time it is opened. I have counted more than 70+ times trying to get the app to open at one time. No matter what I do, the app closes out immediately. I have cleared the app cache & data, repeatedly. Uninstalled then reinstalled the app, soft resets, updates and STILL the app immediately closes when I open it. On the rare occasion it finally does open, it freezes, ignores orders placed yet still charges for the orders. This app is a mess.

Horrible app errors at every turn, app wouldn't let me pick a paymentethod with an offer applied to my order, then when that was sorted out the offer itself caused another error not allowing me to checkout. Then the cvv code confirmation hits an error. Fast food just turned into a 30 kinite headache and I still haven't ordered. Guess I won't be buying 50 bucks in food at your restaurant tonight. Deleting this terrible app and going to Taco Bell, their app actually works.

There needs to be a way to turn off the extraneous notifications in the app. I want to be able to receive notifications for my order, but I absolutely do not want the advertising notifications that the app sends daily, if not multiple times a day. App works slowly when trying to ordwr as well.

One of the worst apps I have ever downloaded! You can never load one of the offers it always gives you an error message and tells you that you need to add food to your cart when there's already food in your cart. Also if you try to change your credit card number it gives you an error message and won't let you change that as well. I reached out to customer service they text me back and forth for 20 minutes and literally didn't South my issue. The people who designed this for them should be fired

The app is working nicely, with the Rewards and Coupons on account. But there were a couple recent changes not for the better. I understand if there's now a premium charge for cheese sauce on breakfast sandwiches where that's not already included, but now you can't remove bacon from the free Baconator (with purchase). I guess you get what you pay for.

Twice now, at least 2 weeks apart, I tried getting into the app so I could use it. It shows me to create a login. (I did all of the following on both occasions.) After wasting my time filling in the blanks, it shows that email is already being used. I back out of everything and add my email to login. Guess what? Then it shows me I have to create a login to start using the app! No more. App is going to be deleted as soon as I complete this post.
And the award for the absolute worst application goes to.. Wendy's. It's not so hard. Try the McDonald's application, then imitate it. Can't lead? Follow.

Seems to not work more often than it works & now even though I deleted the old version of the app and downloaded the new version, the updated newer version of the app wont install properly!! UPDATE TO REVIEW: Got a message from Wendy's Customer Service with a phone number to call but when I called the number tonight, I was told by the representative that she was told to read a statement put out by their IT Dept that stated that some phone models are just not compatible with new updated app v
replyContent: That's definitely not okay! Please give us a call at 888-624-8140 so we can troubleshoot this issue!

content: I don't know if it's just me, but every time I use this app, the employees ALWAYS have to check up on my app again THEN start preparing the meal. Isn't picking up the food supposed to be ready on a certain time to be ready when the customer arrives? It seems like this is the only app that doesn't do that. Seems like a waste of time using the app and would rather just order in person since the time waiting on food is basically the same thing.

The app never let me to agree on the term and condition. The OK button is grayed out and can't be clicked. When I try to login, it never remembers. The app kept asking me to login. The app is useless to me. I tried to uninstall and reinstall several times and nothing changes. Worthless app. Love the food but not the app.

You might have better luck placing order at the store instead of using the app. I order the breakfast and they made me wait 15 min and can't wait longer cause I had to go to work. The store employees said they are not able to cancel cause they cannot control the app purchase and when I contact the app customer care they cannot do anything cause the store already accepted the order. It's been 11 days and it's still on going process of getting a refund and they still let me run around.

Update 12.1.20 - mobile order is broken, freezing - mobile order takes upto 30 minutes to get to a restaurant - restauranta don't see the same name you have on your phone - the menu is confusing between deals and offers - order experience is aweful , the app has place 2 orders with the press of one button and it's always trying to reorder old items when I'm trying to input new ones ... Very frustrating experience... If the development team would actually use this app , they would know what sux

It's fairly simple to use the app and place your order. What the app is lacking however, is the ability to modify your drinks with added flavors if your location has a Coke Freestyle machine, and there is no option for "light ice" but there's a choice for "extra ice". Never in my life have I heard someone ask for more ice, and less drink. If these options are added to the app, it would make it much better and give the feeling of a more complete order.
Completely unusable. Cant even register an account. ("Sorry there was an error". Gee thanks for the info.) No support.

Your app has not worked for months. Website said it was open for dine in, arrived and was closed. App has not worked for months, always get an error was detected .....this location may not be able to accept mobile orders at this time please try again, used to work fine, now not so much. Same with every other Wendy 's location.

My opinion of Wendy's just got lower because of this app, way lower. Try to create login (using email) . Get to last page and get "customer_ID already exists in mapping table". (very user friendly error message Wendy's, BTW). So I figure I maybe already have a login (not probable). So I try to login with email and then press "forgot password" link. That causes another error. The quality of this app is in direct relation to the quality of Wendy's food in last several years.

worst app, worst customer service both at the restaurant & through the 1800 # smfh. I was double charged, spent over a half hr on hold then had to call back the next morning. she did inform me id be getting a refund for the first charge once its processed BUT the app does NOT make you aware of this when adding items.. The manager at the store couldn't help me. my food was cold & they put two WHOLE slices of bacon on my baked potato! the burgers were cold. so now I have to wait for an call.
App location doesn't refresh soon enough for geo fencing. You can be at restaurant nfirnanciuple minutes before it refreshes. Offer option to refresh location in order approved screen?

This app needs work. I live in a basement suite so I don't get coupons in the mail. Not only are the in-app coupons lame (i.e. $2 off meals) but after selecting a baconator coupon it magically disappeared as if I redeemed it, never to be found again. And filing a complaint in-app requires restaurant location specific info that is totally irrelevant to this bug. Please fix, please.

App is pretty well garbage. It takes FOREVER to load the checkout. Like seriously you will be waiting several minutes each time you check your cart for it to load. Ridiculous. If you need to visit your cart several times add 2-3 minutes per visit to your order time. Wendy's should be paying me to use this thing it wastes so much time.
Worst app keeps crashing and taking all my darn rewards and offers. Usually at a time when I could use the discount..happen tooooo many times and it sucks.

How am I supppsed to use the app if I can't create an account? Every time I try to create the account it tells me the password doesn't meet the minimum requirements at the end. However, when creating the password I am seeing that all requirements are fulfilled! This is a frustrating experience.

I used it for 10 seconds and all ready dont like it. Why would it ask for my location then not find a near by store?? Then I need to know the address of a store to search one??? No thank off to a different fast food chane

I ordered breakfast on the app. It was cutting it close to 10:22 (the latest time the app told me I could check in) and I was delayed by a train. I got to the Wendy's and they still made my order; It was warm and tasted great. Very good experience (it was the Lindbergh Springfield, IL location) Edit: Still happy with the app although I wish there were more coupons for free stuff when you buy something. I got to try the Pub Fries because of a coupon and they were pretty good!
This app won't let me place my order every time I use it. It keeps saying that their is an error. I would just order online from your phone's browser.

This app is garbage. It processed a payment only a couple of times and now it reverses all of our payments. My husband and I have over 600 points we can't redeem. Its difficult to use because the store address covers the checkout bag. When you change stores, you have to change your order even though they have the exact same item.

App worked great for a while. My last two trips didn't add my rewards points. 2nd to last trip i spent $30 and didn't get any of those points. Just now i spent $10 and same thing. Spoke to store manager both times and was told the same thing that they couldn't do anything. Two different locations about 30 miles away.

App is nothing but worthless space on my phone. Completely broken no matter if I uninstall, restart, or reinstall, or try to make new accounts (it fails that). Qr code refuses to load, offers are blank, and my points value is non-existent even though I had over a thousand points saved. This is the only way to make the food not be overpriced. Hope I get a response for a fix because reddit gave nothing.

While I enjoy this app, it is missing just one thing in my opinion. As far as I can tell, there is no way to order your drink with light ice/no ice. I prefer to have my drinks without ice and it would be helpful if I could order them that way. The app already allows you to make adjustments to your sandwich, so it would be great to see that kind of consideration towards your drink.

Pretty bad for a mobile ordering app if you can't place in-app orders. It is stuck at an endless loop at the location selection. I tap "select a location" and then I find the nearest Wendy's (which it says does mobile ordering), select "start your order" and then it just returns to the location selection screen and says I have to enter my location. It is quite frustrating.

The app ordering experience is okay and there are nice deals and rewards. However, the refund policy is very annoying. It took 3 weeks and 5 conversations to get a $5 meal back after the restaurant couldn't give me my order because they couldn't see it. Other fast food apps can refund you after a single email explaining what went wrong.
Watch out! App kept repeatedly doubling or tripling things in my cart. Once I removed all the extra items everything worked out fine though.

They don't make the meal until your there. Then why have the app. Will trigger the app, by saying I'm there early as I know it takes time to make for a family of 6. Get here and they still haven't made the food, because they don't see the order unless someone is at the register. Save us the hassle and look at how Starbucks runs there program. Stuff is ready when you walk in.

The app doesn't work right. If I go back after selecting a reward I can't find the reward again even though I didn't use it. The app also charged me twice for an order. I tried to get in contact with Wendy's and it's way intentionally difficult... Horrible experience all around

This app is awful. My favorite part is I like to get my Wendy's on the go; 1. The drive through people can't figure out how to scan your code or they're afraid due to covid. 2. So then ask for the receipt to manually get your credit, YOU FILL OUT EVERYTHING AND THEN IT ASKS FOR A PICTURE OF YOUR RECEIPT, BUT THAT DOESNT WORK. SO I UNINSTALLED TO FIX, NOW IT CANT REMEMBER MY LOG IN. TERRIBLE AND FRUSTRSTING APP. GET LOST WENDY'S YOU ARE THE WEAKEST LINK!

App only works once in a while and when you do have an issue customer care is about as dumb as a box of rocks when the app does work half the time the people get the order wrong anyway so I've just decided if I ever eat at Wendy's again after multiple times of people forgetting to put my whole order in the bag before they give it to me I'll just order through the speaker box because when you do have an issue customer care takes a week to get back to you and then they're impatient as hell deali

Tried to order twice and just showed error twice saying they don't have the food. Still charged me twice for the order. Strongly advise against using this app they'll just charge you and give you nothinf

This app will not allow the use of your gift card if your order is more than the gift card value. E.g. if you have a $20 gift card, but your order is $20.50, you cannot use a credit card to pay the $0.50 residual. Instead you are forced to load minimum of $10.00 into your account before drawing $0.50 from the loaded amount. On top of that, Wendy sold my phone number to telemarketers. Since signing up for an account this morning, I received 8 spam phone calls in 4 hours time. NoT COOL.

Works well. Needs option for sweet tea though. I either have to risk getting an unsweet tea or they have to pour out the unsweet tea they fix or hope someone else orders it soon after me. The south has a lot of Wendy's. They should know better.

Received a service error on adding a credit card to the account. The error doesn't point to anything wrong. Very, very poor programming on the developer. Will fix my rating, but after reading a lot of problems with the app and getting contact seems doubtful.

What a mess!!! Where the hell is breakfast ? I kept scrolling around and then somehow it finally appeared....now it wont let me add it to my order!! Can you say "rewrite"? This app is frustrating the F out of me..Trash it and start the f over! Save yourself the frustration and just go in to Wendys and order.

Well I am 4 for 4. Since downloading the app, I have tried to scan to earn rewards 4 times it did not work. I then tried to get a hold of customer service thru the app. Yeah good luck with that. There does not seem to be a way to enter the receipt information to account for the QR Scan code never working. Wendy's really needs to revamp this app so it actually works. At least my Chik Fil A app works everytime.

I just downloaded the app last night, right before going to Wendy's! I can't even enroll...states "Oops...something went wrong! Please try again later"! What's the purpose of creating an app, when no one can enroll, order, check rewards, etc? Therefore, I can only rate this app a 1 star ðŸŒŸ!
The app does not work properly. I put items in my cart then when I go to check out it says that the cart is empty but I can see the items there.
Pops up notifications telling me I can get a free sandwich and there is no such promo. Tried to use it to get deals and discounts but there were no discounts worth using.
I have only got this to work once. I have the cashier scan my phone, but can never get the coupons to work and never get rewards points.
The app is useless and redundant if you already have delivery service app because the "SPECIAL OFFERS" DO NOT TRANSFER OVER FROM THE WENDY'S APP TO YOUR DELIVERY SERVICE APP ! WASTE OF TIME !

Nothing works in the app. No delivery options even though it says they deliver. I talked to customer service and they just kept telling me to uninstall and reinstall the app even though I literally JUST installed it for the first time. Then the agent asked me what phone I used and then told me its "specific issue to your device - we have just tested to confirm". I use a Samsung Galaxy S9. Then the agent ended our chat. Brutal.

I really enjoy this app. Wendys is one of the few fast few restaurants I like to eat at. I have one problem that is causing me to rate them so low. Most of the Wendy's near me have the coke freestyle machine. Which offers Diet Dr. Pepper and Sprite zero. My favorite sodas being that I'm a diabetic. Whenever I order pickup its for drive thru. The drink options aren't open for Diet Dr Pepper or Sprite Zero. So going through the drive through I ask for them to change it to and its rarely done.
Great way to order, pay ahead and customize your order. They also offer great daily deals and points everytime you purchase food.

When you have a offer for free breakfast baconator with Any purchase then that should be it. Try to check out with the offer and a coffee and it says it has to be a la carte or something stupid. I clicked on the offer on my app. Should apply pretty simple

The app itself is great, better than the average fast food app. Only complaint was a random 2AM ad notification. But using for mobile orders has been rough. Local stores have not provided adequate training for mobile orders. Employees have either not understood how to find my order or argue that it was already picked up when it turned out it was mistakenly sitting at the drive thru window isntead of in store pickup. Only had one good experience with mobile orders out of 8 visits.

Won't let you look at anything they offer unless you sign up and give them your info first. It should be the opposit you should let people check it out and then decide if they want to give you their info and create an account

I went to use the coupon for the free chicken sandwich with any purchase. I scanned my QR code at the window and the cashier told me my new total. What she said was correct, but my card was charged for the chicken sandwich, or my total before the coupon was applied. Moral of the story, the coupon was pseudo applied and they did nothing to ameliorate the situation. The sandwich wasn't even that good, but that's not the apps fault.
Love that you can customize order. Menu is current to the restaurant offerings. Beats McDonald's app.
App doesnt work. You can fill your cart but cant check out. It just loads for 15 minutes then says there was an error.

Unable to create account via email. Submitted password has 1 upper case letter, 2 lower case letters, 1 punctuation symbol and between 6-10 numbers. It meets the listed requirements but it's rejected both on the app and website. Edit: app checks a requirement when using a period, but won't accept them. Leaving at 1 star for terrible inputs.

Pretty bad logic built into the app. It offers coupons/discounts but sometimes won't apply it to your total. They haven't done a good job testing things. Also, even if you are standing at the restaurant it won't let you order breakfast after 10:25.

What is the point of ordering ahead when I literally had to wait in line at the drive thru for 33 min. Dining room could be open for take out at least. Last time they didn't even have the food I ordered, couldn't get a refund. After 17 days I got a replacement order that wasnt correct. Wendy's need to get it together. There should be an alternate way to pick up food you ordered from the app. It's rather useless if I still wait over 30 minutes!
Will not add credit card. Charges my card then kicks it back. States that I should check authorization info although that's clearly not the issue. Please fix

This app literally never works. I spent weeks trying to get it to set up with Google or Facebook but because my name has an accent in it, it would never let me accept the T&C's or go back to change the spelling of my name. I finally got it to set up with my email address and when I reset my phone, now it won't let me sign in. It keeps saying can't create an account, but the account is already created and I'm signing in, not creating.

Garbage app that's only good for coupons... when they cut those out, I'll delete it. Ordering ahead defeats the whole purpose when I still have to wait in drive-thru behind 12 other vehicles. My order also isn't started until I have arrived. As much as I dislike McDonald's, the developer of this app could learn from McDonald's. At least they have spots to pick up preordered food.
